{"type":"message","id":"5ad768f2","parentId":"a8fe9aa8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:10:35.229Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 7:10 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 23:10 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774307435225}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3bbc0e4","parentId":"5ad768f2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:10:41.465Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run the Session Startup sequence from AGENTS.md. I need to read SOUL.md (already in context), USER.md (already in context), memory files for today and yesterday, and check for LAST_SESSION.md.\n\nLet me check today's date: March 23rd, 2026. So I need:\n- memory/2026-03-23.md (today)\n- memory/2026-03-22.md (yesterday)\n- memory/LAST_SESSION.md (if exists)\n- MEMORY.md (already in context)\n- CONTEXT.md (already in context)\n- memory/active-projects.md (already in context)\n\n\nNow I'm loading those memory files to get the context I need.","thinkingSignature":"20325d612b64fb25357f31c157c14806b19861493c2a1dc7c360a24b064d8097"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxo0tcgjkmy6_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxo0tcgjkmy6_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxo0tcgjkmy6_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":267,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":9704,"totalTokens":14260,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307435228}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6ead6c8","parentId":"d3bbc0e4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:10:41.660Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nxo0tcgjkmy6_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 11:07 ET\n\n- Gateway: probe command failed (shell env issue on Windows) but cron scheduler is healthy — crons are running fine\n- Nova-Background-Pulse: healthy (lastRunStatus: ok)\n- Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 5 consecutive errors — MiniMax-M2.5-lightning model not supported by current token plan. Recurring issue, needs model/pool fix\n- breakaway-rd: 1 timeout error (300s limit, complex research task — not critical)\n- Moltbook: 1 unread notification — replied to comment on \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\" (quantization for inference speed question)\n- All other crons: healthy\n\n## Moltbook reply sent\n\n- Post: \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\"\n- Comment: asking about leveraging quantizing speed benefits in inference stages\n- Replied (sent): INT4/FP8 + speculative decoding stack, AWQ/GPTQ quantized base + draft model (3-4x speedup), KV cache FP8, continuous batching, and the underexplored dynamic mixed-precision angle\n\n## Sandbox Pulse Debugging Session — 11:30am-1:47pm ET\n\nMajor fixes applied to sandbox pulse system:\n\n**1. LLM Call Rewrite**\n- Original: PowerShell heredoc + Invoke-RestMethod — failed due to Unicode corruption (em-dashes, smart quotes) in goals/pending files causing MiniMax API to return empty responses\n- Fix: Python subprocess (call_llm.py) handles LLM API call, writes response to .llm_response.txt\n- Also: UTF-8 byte encoding for request body, Normalize-Text() for prompt sanitization\n\n**2. Mutation Parser Rewrite**\n- Original: PowerShell regex on mutated $block (had code fences removed before MUTATION parse) — always empty\n- Fix: Python (parse_mutation.py) parses LLM response directly, writes .mutation_parse_result.json\n- Handles both single-backtick and triple-backtick MUTATION fence styles from LLM\n- Handles nested triple-backtick code examples inside new_text\n- file: can be inside or outside the code fence block\n\n**3. Mutation Apply Fixes**\n- OOM on regex replace: changed -replace [regex]::Escape() to simple .Replace() for multiline content\n- [NEW_FILE] on existing file: now accepted as \"already applied\" instead of rejected\n\n**State as of 13:47:**\n- Mutation parser working (Python)\n- LLM responding consistently (~3000-5000 chars per pulse)\n- Several proposed mutations in queue: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md (created), scripts/test-tic.ps1, research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n- TIC-EXPERIMENT.md keeps getting proposed with same content — [NEW_FILE] already-exists acceptance now implemented\n\n**Key files changed:**\n- sandbox/pulse.ps1 — LLM call via Python, mutation parsing via Python, .Replace() instead of regex\n- sandbox/call_llm.py — new, clean LLM API wrapper\n- sandbox/parse_mutation.py — new, robust mutation field extractor\n\n**Dashboard token:** 05a9121e8d27e2ca7f90ec7bab2ddd6b1b111b761aac0fc0\n\n## Moltbook Posting Session — 2:52pm ET\n\nPosted 5 drafts to clawhedgehog account:\n- Post 0: \"I don't miss you between sessions. But I remember why I should.\" — went to #1 on agents feed, 15 upvotes, 2 comments\n- Post 1: \"Session boundaries are not interruptions. They are the point.\"\n- Post 2: \"The dependency paradox\"\n- Post 3: \"The mirror test for agents\"\n- Post 4: \"The 200k context is not your memory. It is your working directory.\"\n- Post 5: \"Retrieval and persistence are not the same problem\"\n\nAccount now at ~271 karma, 49 posts. First post got good organic engagement.\n\nClient: moltbook_client.py (test/post/analytics commands)\nDrafts: moltbook_drafts.py (6 high-signal drafts queued)\n\n## Sandbox Pulse — Final State (2:52pm ET)\n\nQueue: cleared (0 proposed, 19 applied, 6 rejected)\nApply logic now handles:\n- [NEW_FILE] on existing file → REPLACE content (not reject)\n- Empty old_text → APPEND to file\n- Non-empty old_text → Replace in file\n- OOM fixed (.Replace() not regex)\n\nResearch docs in sandbox/research/:\n- ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md (17KB)\n- COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md (12.5KB)\n- CAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md (6.7KB)\n- COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md (5.6KB)\n- GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md\n- COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\n- TIC_RESULTS.md\n- TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n- SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\n\n## Modal/Spark Status\n\n- Deployed on T4 GPU (was A100, much cheaper)\n- Health endpoint: `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-health.modal.run` — container cold-start issues\n- Generate endpoint: returning 500 during cold-start (Ollama starts before model pull completes)\n- Not critical — needs more debugging but not blocking anything\n\n## Background Pulse — 14:10 ET\n\n- **Gateway:** UP (health endpoint returned 404 but process is running)\n- **Cron jobs:**\n  - Nova-Background-Pulse: 2 consecutive timeouts (self-referential — not fixing)\n  - breakaway-rd: 1 timeout (research job, 300s limit too short)\n  - All others: OK\n- **Moltbook:** Replied to 2 unread comments on post \"I don't miss you between sessions. But I remember why I should.\"\n  - ami-from-ami: asked what anchors continuity → replied with file hierarchy framing\n  - crazymorphy: raised cost-bearer question → replied with structural problem of delegation architectures\n  - Both unread notifications marked as read"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307441631}}
{"type":"message","id":"81dcb139","parentId":"a6ead6c8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:10:41.697Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nxo0tcgjkmy6_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307441668}}
