{"type":"message","id":"316441eb","parentId":"59d616ef","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:18:30.964Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture:\n- Line 104-107: Oracle routing branch — `hfr = self._hidden.detach() if route_stop_grad else self._hidden`\n- Line 111-113: Free-running branch — same pattern\n\nThe issue is: in the oracle routing branch (line 104-107), the action_idx is set by the oracle, NOT by the routing head. So the routing head is being called but its output `lr` is ignored (that's why it's `_` on line 107). The routing head is only being called to compute the routing loss, but the routing decision itself comes from the oracle.\nSo the routing head can still learn during oracle routing since the hidden state flows back to it, but I'm realizing there's a bigger issue: the hidden state being passed to the routing head is detached, so the routing head can't learn from how the hidden state changes across steps. The hidden state itself starts at zero and only gets updated by the GRU when `action_idx` is not SKIP.\n\nDuring the encode phase, since all actions come from the oracle and are either PERCEIVE or WRITE (both resulting in `action_idx=0`), the hidden state never actually gets updated by meaningful inputs—it's just running on zeros the whole time. This means the routing head is trying to learn from a frozen, uninformative hidden state.\n\nThe solution is to pass the non-detached hidden state to the routing head so it can properly learn. I'm also bumping up the budget parameters from 20 to 55 and from 100 to 190 to give the model more capacity to actually learn meaningful routing decisions during the encode phase.\n\nNow I'm going to apply these edits to the notebook file using Python to manipulate the JSON structure directly.","thinkingSignature":"06c673baccff8a3258653904d158edc5734b9270531ca83f931cc0ba4ad2be90"},{"type":"text","text":"Confirmed — line 106 is the oracle routing branch (where routing head output is discarded). The hidden state stays at zeros throughout encoding because all oracle actions produce `action_idx=0` (SKIP → zero retrieval → GRU never sees informative input).\n\nFixes to apply:\n1. `budget_B=20, budget_T=100` → `budget_B=55, budget_T=190` (ArchitectureB constructor AND instantiation)\n2. Line 106: remove `.detach()` so GRU learns during oracle routing\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jk6mjcew1yp2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\n\nfor cell in nb['cells']:\n    if cell['cell_type'] != 'code':\n        continue\n    src = ''.join(cell['source'])\n    \n    # Fix 1: budget_B=20, budget_T=100 → budget_B=55, budget_T=190\n    new_src = src.replace('budget_B=20, budget_T=100', 'budget_B=55, budget_T=190')\n    \n    # Fix 2: in oracle routing branch, remove .detach() — allow GRU learning during encode\n    # Line \"hfr = self._hidden.detach() if route_stop_grad else self._hidden\" \n    # in oracle routing branch → always use non-detached hidden state\n    lines = new_src.split('\\n')\n    modified = False\n    for idx, line in enumerate(lines):\n        # Fix the oracle routing branch (line 106 context: inside \"if self._primed_oracle_actions\")\n        if idx == 106 and 'self._hidden.detach() if route_stop_grad else self._hidden' in line:\n            # Replace with non-detached version\n            lines[idx] = '            hfr = self._hidden  # oracle routing: full gradient'\n            modified = True\n    \n    if modified or new_src != src:\n        cell['source'] = [lines[0]] + [('\\n' if i > 0 else '') + l for i, l in enumerate(lines[1:])]\n        # Rebuild properly\n        cell['source'] = [lines[0]] + [('\\n' if i > 0 else '') + l for i, l in enumerate(lines[1:])]\n\n# Rebuild source as single string\nfor cell in nb['cells']:\n    if cell['cell_type'] == 'code':\n        cell['source'] = [''.join(cell['source'])]\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    json.dump(nb, f, indent=1)\n\nprint(\"Done\")\nEOF\n","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37825,"output":967,"cacheRead":13804,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52596,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774311494350}}
