{"type":"message","id":"108a7090","parentId":"2b1ffcdb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:19:06.713Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both changes are applied. Now let me also check if the `div_reg` (diversity regularizer) computation frequency should be increased to every step instead of once per episode. But that might be an optimization, not a bug. Let me not touch it for now and focus on the core fixes.\n\nAlso, I should update the Phase 1 training to use a smaller learning rate since the model now gets gradients during the encode phase too (which it didn't before). But again, let me not change too many things at once and see if the basic fixes work first.\n\nLet me now write a quick summary of what was fixed and the expected impact, and tell Zach to re-run Phase 1.\n\n\nThe diversity loss is only computed once per episode with the final hidden state, so during encoding the routing head's codebook never learns which codes fire at each step. Since the diversity loss is already small (0.06), this might not be critical. I'll mention it to Zach but let him decide if it's worth addressing.\n\nLet me also check if there's an issue with the DiversityRegularizer. It's called with the detached hidden state, which means the gradients don't flow back to the encoder. This might be fine since the diversity loss is small (0.06), but it's worth noting.\n\nSo my fixes:\n1. `budget_B=55, budget_T=190` — allows all 50 KV pairs to be written during encoding\n2. Remove `.detach()` in oracle routing — allows GRU to learn during encoding\n\nThe accuracy ceiling was 50% (only 20 out of 50 KV pairs stored). With budget=55, all 50 can be stored. Combined with proper GRU learning, accuracy should improve significantly.\n\nI should also increase the number of pretraining epochs to 3000-5000 since the model now has more to learn with the proper gradients flowing.","thinkingSignature":"572b06ac9a047db6aae10fd1f8dc34ab4616deec7915b991045ed8c65ec8b67c"},{"type":"text","text":"Both fixes applied:\n- `budget_B=55, budget_T=190` — all 50 KV pairs can now be written during encoding\n- Oracle routing branch now uses non-detached hidden state — GRU learns to form memories during encode\n\nOne more thing worth flagging: the diversity regularizer (`div_loss`) is computed only once per episode using the final hidden state, so the router's encoder never learns which codes fire at each step during encoding. It's small (0.06) so probably not the bottleneck, but you could fix it by moving the `diversity_loss` call inside the step loop. Happy to add that if Phase 1 still plateaus.\n\nGo ahead and re-run Phase 1 — accuracy should be much better now that all 50 KV pairs get stored."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40167,"output":543,"cacheRead":13804,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54514,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774311534611}}
