{"type":"message","id":"19f14240","parentId":"0496a84d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:31:05.476Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but `os.getcwd()` will be the directory where the notebook server is running, which might not be the notebook directory. Actually, that's fine - wandb will create its run files in that directory. Let me run the fix.Actually, I realize there's a bigger issue. The cell 6 currently has:\n```python\nimport os\nimport wandb\n_wandb_key = os.environ.get(\"WANDB_API_KEY\", \"\")\nif _wandb_key:\n    wandb.init(project=\"srmoe\", name=\"srmoe-run\", dir=os.getcwd(),\n               settings=wandb.Settings(_stats_wait_seconds=10))\n    print(f\"Wandb initialized: {wandb.run.url if hasattr(wandb, 'run') else 'ok'}\")\nelse:\n    print(\"WANDB_API_KEY not found, skipping wandb\")\n\n\n```\n\nBut `os.getcwd()` in a notebook context returns the working directory of the notebook server, not necessarily the notebook's directory. That's fine for wandb files though. The real thing I need to verify is whether Zach's notebook environment actually has `wandb` installed - if it doesn't, the import will fail and nothing else matters. I should check if the imports cell handles this or if we need to add a pip install command first.\n\nActually, the imports cell uses `subprocess.run` to pip install numpy quietly, so I could do the same for wandb. Let me add that to cell 1 instead, since that's where the dependencies are already being set up.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"1d661c2e5fb4f83232bef106447302878bbdb6c07d3d3cb15d265229e2a1b2ec"},{"type":"text","text":"Also — cell 1 installs numpy via pip, but not wandb. Let me add wandb install there too so it works:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ojcvk8kdt5b8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\fix_wandb_full.py","content":"import json, os\n\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    