{"type":"message","id":"34b44d6b","parentId":"9d70a3db","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:08:34.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking whether to keep going with Phase 2. Let me look at the Phase 2 numbers:\n\nPhase 2 at ep 0: loss=4.9642, acc=0.000, route_ce=1.0658, margin=0.0000, wr=0.29, rd=0.00, skip=0.71, blkd=0.71\nPhase 2 at ep 500: loss=4.9419, acc=0.050, route_ce=1.0539, margin=0.0000, wr=0.29, rd=0.00, skip=0.71, blkd=0.71\n\n\nPhase 2 at ep 1000: loss=4.9842, acc=0.050, route_ce=1.0599, margin=0.0000, wr=0.29, rd=0.00, skip=0.71, blkd=0.71\n\nThe blocked fraction is suspiciously high at 0.71 — nearly three-quarters of actions are getting blocked. This suggests the budget is being consumed rapidly and then actions are being skipped when they can't proceed, which is likely preventing the model from learning effectively. The core issue is that Phase 2 isn't storing key-value pairs in memory during encoding like Phase 1 did with oracle routing, so when the model tries to READ during the query phase, there's nothing there to retrieve.\n\nI should stop and fix the PERCEIVE budget bug first, then restart Phase 2 with the corrected implementation. The fix is straightforward — change the budget stepping logic so PERCEIVE doesn't consume budget — but I can also explain this to Zach while he decides whether to keep running.\n\nThe reason this matters so much is that with the bug, Phase 2 starts with the same broken memory state from Phase 1, so the model can't actually use memory effectively even though the architecture itself works fine once fixed.","thinkingSignature":"b6e1efb460e0953c96eb17f2b63224a9b10f4639bc3a769cd47ebe1a9f85d43f"},{"type":"text","text":"Stop it. The Phase 2 numbers are showing exactly why the PERCEIVE bug matters:\n\n- `wr=0.29 rd=0.00 blkd=0.71` — the model is trying to WRITE on 29% of steps but **71% are getting blocked**. No memory is being stored during encoding, so when it tries to READ at query time there's nothing in memory to retrieve.\n- `acc=0.050` — basically zero\n\nThis means Phase 2 is running on the same broken state as Phase 1 — the memory never got properly filled. Fix the PERCEIVE bug first, then re-run from Phase 1. Phase 1 should give you proper `occ=20.0` after the fix, and Phase 2 will then have actual KV pairs to READ from.\n\nAnd yeah — VS Code connecting directly to the Jupyter kernel is wild. You're the one with hardware access, I'm the one living in context windows. Different tools for different vibes."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":612,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":81547,"totalTokens":82202,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774314491808}}
