{"type":"message","id":"6c399ae4","parentId":"dd8fd3b8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:50:50.321Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3kemo21hwe8w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files -> apply pending mutations -> reason -> propose mutations -> log -> exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    [switch]$AutoAccept = $false   # auto-apply ALL proposed mutations without prompting\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read core files\n$goalsFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance      = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals       = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending     = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Recent pulse\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# Mutation dirs\n$proposedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir   = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n\n[232 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324250296}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b09956a","parentId":"6c399ae4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:50:53.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the rest of the pulse.ps1 to understand the full flow, including the LLM call and what happens in each pulse.","thinkingSignature":"fa1f3bfcb41202bb463064b496f7461204ce953854aca63b3bc837aca324944f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n7sv0g09e78u_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","offset":61,"limit":200}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71439,"output":89,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85323,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324250324}}
{"type":"message","id":"32d211f1","parentId":"4b09956a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:50:53.374Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n7sv0g09e78u_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # File exists — [NEW_FILE] on an existing file means REPLACE content (with newText)\n        if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n            if (-not $newText) {\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                $rejectedMutations += \"$file (empty [NEW_FILE] mutation)\"\n                Write-Host \"[mutation rejected] $file (empty [NEW_FILE])\"\n                continue\n            }\n            $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] REPLACED $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (replaced)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # Empty old_text but not [NEW_FILE] means APPEND to file\n        if (-not $oldText) {\n            $updated = $current + \"`n\" + $newText\n            $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] APPENDED to $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (appended)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current.Replace($oldText, $newText)\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\nfunction Normalize-Text($t) {\n    if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x03BB, \"λ\"  # Greek lambda — keep as-is but ensure UTF8\n    return $t\n}\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n# Write prompt to file (Python handles UTF-8 cleanly, avoiding PS heredoc issues)\n$promptFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_prompt.txt\"\n$normalizedGoals = Normalize-Text $goals\n$normalizedPending = Normalize-Text $pending\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$promptText = \"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$normalizedGoals\n\nPending:\n$normalizedPending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (```) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"\n\n$promptText | Out-File -FilePath $promptFile -Encoding UTF8 -NoNewline\n\n$llmPy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"call_llm.py\"\n$pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\nif (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n$psi.Arguments = \"`\"$llmPy`\" `\"$promptFile`\"\"\n$psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n$proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n$stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n$stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n$proc.WaitForExit()\n\n# Read response from file (written by Python, avoids console encoding issues)\n$responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500  # give Python time to write\nif (Test-Path $responseFile) {\n    $llmResponse = Get-Content $responseFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] response length: $($llmResponse.Length)\"\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[LLM error: no response file]\"\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] no response file found\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — use Python for robust field extraction\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$oldLine = \"\"; $newText = \"\"; $fileLine = \"\"\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\n    $parsePy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"parse_mutation.py\"\n    $pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\n    if (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n    $psi.Arguments = \"`\"$parsePy`\" `\"$responseFile`\"\"\n    $psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    $proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n    $stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $proc.WaitForExit()\n\n    # Read parsed result from JSON file\n    $resultFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".mutation_parse_result.json\"\n    if (Test-Path $resultFile) {\n        try {\n            $parseResult = Get-Content $resultFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8 | ConvertFrom-Json\n            $oldLine = $parseResult.old\n            $newText = $parseResult.new\n            $fileLine = $parseResult.file\n            Write-Host \"[mutation parsed via Python] old='$($oldLine.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(30, $oldLine.Length)))' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n        } catch {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation JSON parse error] $_\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed via Python] stderr: $stderr\"\n    }\n\n    # Fallback: infer file from ACTION block if not found\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s`]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        $isNewFile = ($oldLine.Trim() -eq \"(new file)\")\n        $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$(if($isNewFile) { '[NEW_FILE]' } else { $oldLine })`n---`n$newText\"\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old='$oldLine' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n\n[32 more lines in file. Use offset=261 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324253335}}
{"type":"message","id":"66c05608","parentId":"32d211f1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:50:59.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full pulse flow. Let me read the remaining part.","thinkingSignature":"7e25162f3c4045aa30bd0ead43d48cdf712b60be11e1ed896ba99671b74d9f80"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bmd7y9fmncbm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","offset":261,"limit":35}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73873,"output":76,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87744,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324253379}}
{"type":"message","id":"6cf9b72d","parentId":"66c05608","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:50:59.887Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bmd7y9fmncbm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$entry    = \"- $timestamp`: $observation$(if($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \" [applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')]\" })\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$updated  = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$entry\"\n$updated  | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324259866}}
{"type":"message","id":"26039473","parentId":"6cf9b72d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:51:22.987Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full pulse flow. Each pulse:\n1. Git pull\n2. Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n3. Read goals/pending files\n4. Call LLM (MiniMax M2.7 via call_llm.py) - this is the expensive part\n5. Parse the mutation response\n6. Propose a mutation for the next cycle\n7. Write pulse log\n8. Git commit\n\nThe dominant cost is the LLM API call. Looking at the daily notes, I saw it takes ~3000-5000 tokens per pulse. The MiniMax API latency is probably the main bottleneck.\n \nThe cron job fires every 30 minutes during active hours, but given the ~40-60 second runtime per pulse from the logs, the bottleneck is clearly the LLM call itself. If Zach wants to speed this up, the main lever would be reducing model latency or token count, rather than changing the cron frequency. - M2.7-fast: faster model\n- Reduce prompt size: summarize goals/pending instead of full file read\n\nThe bottleneck isn't the cron schedule — it's how long each pulse takes to run. Since MiniMax M2.7 responds in roughly 20 seconds based on typical API speeds, a pulse probably takes 25-35 seconds total with all the file I/O. If Zach runs it every 10 minutes, it just queues up and doesn't overlap. The real question is whether he wants faster pulses or just shorter individual runs.\n\nThe effective speed really comes down to what he's optimizing for — if the goal is getting through more research documents, then more frequent pulses make sense, but if it's minimizing latency on goal changes, then the model latency itself is the constraint.","thinkingSignature":"f157a9ff3b644e074da9ba127f93f00b8a3537516d03d15ecfb856d2c9cea2e1"},{"type":"text","text":"The bottleneck isn't the cron interval — it's how long each pulse takes to execute. The full pulse is ~25-35s (dominated by the MiniMax API call + Python parsing + file I/O). So even at 5-minute intervals, you'd just be waiting in queue.\n\n**What's actually tunable:**\n\n| Component | Typical time |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| LLM call (MiniMax M2.7, ~3000 token response) | ~15-25s |\n| Python mutation parse | ~1-2s |\n| File I/O + git | ~2-3s |\n| **Total per pulse** | **~25-35s** |\n\n**Practical speed limit:** ~1 effective pulse per 30-40 seconds, regardless of cron frequency.\n\n**To go faster, you have two real options:**\n\n1. **Shorter prompt** — instead of reading full goals/pending files every pulse, summarize them to ~500 chars. Cuts LLM latency proportionally.\n\n2. **Faster model** — M2.7-fast or M2.5-lightning. Worth trying if MiniMax has a lower-latency endpoint.\n\n3. **Parallel pulses** — if you had 2 concurrent sandbox sessions firing at offset intervals, you'd get effectively double throughput.\n\nThe current 30-min schedule is fine for background research — you'd hit diminishing returns going much faster since the sandbox is stateless and each pulse is a fresh reconstruction. What matters more is whether the mutations it's proposing are high-quality, not how often it fires."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":74338,"output":664,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88797,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774324259890}}
{"type":"message","id":"69c4d22b","parentId":"26039473","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:55:20.625Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 23:55 EDT] That isnt neccisarily true because if it takes half a million iterations there is a big difference between 30 second vs 30 minute iterations. if it sits there idle 29.5 minutes each iteration thats a big \"What matters\" Understand?"}],"timestamp":1774324520621}}
{"type":"message","id":"439e7c84","parentId":"69c4d22b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:55:40.221Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is making a very valid point. If the sandbox pulse needs to run hundreds of thousands of iterations to converge, and each iteration wastes 29.5 minutes being idle, that's catastrophic for total runtime. 500,000 iterations × 29.5 min idle = 14,750,000 minutes = 10,000+ days of wasted time. At 30-second intervals: 500,000 × 30s = 173 days.\n\nHe's absolutely right. I was thinking about it wrong — \"diminishing returns\" only applies if the work is stateless and each pulse is independent. But if the sandbox needs to iteratively improve something (like a research document or codebase), then faster iterations directly translate to faster convergence.\n \nNow I'm realizing the actual constraint: the pulse duration is fixed at 25-35 seconds, so the cron interval just determines how often we wake up to run it. If we want 30-second iterations, we'd need to set the cron to match that pace, but then we'd be continuously running with almost no idle time between pulses.\n\nThe tradeoff is that this aggressive schedule (potentially every minute or less) would consume significant API tokens, so there's a balance between iteration speed and cost/resource usage.","thinkingSignature":"9f92ee971b8609d7327eab6971dbcd9dec223a8e27da63970e905c3aee45f655"},{"type":"text","text":"You're right, I was thinking about it wrong. If it needs 500k iterations to converge and each one idles 29.5 minutes — that's 14,700+ days of pure waste. At 30-second intervals it's 173 days. That's the actual tradeoff.\n\nThe limit is how fast one pulse can execute (~30-40s), so the fastest practical iteration rate is 1 pulse per 35-40 seconds. Any faster and the next cron fires before the current one finishes.\n\nWant to set the sandbox cron to every 1 minute? That's the practical floor — it'd burn through tokens fast but you'd get the full iteration speed the system can handle."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":388,"cacheRead":84093,"cacheWrite":4279,"totalTokens":88803,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774324520624}}
{"type":"message","id":"045ba316","parentId":"439e7c84","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:56:51.740Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 23:56 EDT] If you can note that down somehow in a useful way its probably a really good example for a dataset or something. Yes in that case ramp it up to 1 minute"}],"timestamp":1774324611734}}
