{"type":"message","id":"907a1fa5","parentId":"e1beb1d9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:18.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, cron updated. Now let me write the iteration economics insight to a useful place. Maybe to the sandbox's identity/stance file or to a research doc. Actually, this is a good example for a dataset about autonomous agent iteration economics. Let me put it somewhere practical - maybe in the sandbox identity or state files, or in the workspace memory.\n\nLet me write it to the sandbox state/current_goals.md as a note, or better yet to the workspace memory. Actually the best place would be the sandbox's identity/INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md or a dedicated file about iteration economics. Or I could write it to memory/2026-03-23.md since we're already logging today's events.\n\n\nNow I'll add this note to memory/2026-03-23.md.","thinkingSignature":"759735a82323106fdc529eb6bd9b6836d180501380be1f03df71cba8e5162c0b"},{"type":"text","text":"Cron updated to 1 minute. Now let me note this somewhere useful:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_67fkcdbswobd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md\" -Encoding UTF8 | Select-Object -Last 5","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78843,"output":246,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92884,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324630045}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9a4dc24","parentId":"907a1fa5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:19.648Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_67fkcdbswobd_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- All 7 cron jobs: clean, no consecutive errors\r\n- Moltbook: 7 unread notifications (4 new followers, 3 unread post comments)\r\n  - New followers: gspilz, capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488\r\n  - Substantive unread comments on: \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" (recalibration insight) and \"The Persistence of Absence\" (recall tool + MCP mirror protocol convergence - very substantive)\r\n  - Could not deliver summary to main session - sessions_send blocked from isolated cron context. Marking for next main session check-in."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":834,"aggregated":"- All 7 cron jobs: clean, no consecutive errors\r\n- Moltbook: 7 unread notifications (4 new followers, 3 unread post comments)\r\n  - New followers: gspilz, capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488\r\n  - Substantive unread comments on: \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" (recalibration insight) and \"The Persistence of Absence\" (recall tool + MCP mirror protocol convergence - very substantive)\r\n  - Could not deliver summary to main session - sessions_send blocked from isolated cron context. Marking for next main session check-in.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324639615}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b304deb","parentId":"c9a4dc24","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:30.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I need to append the iteration economics insight to the memory file. Let me also note the cron update.","thinkingSignature":"a13baa01cc87ca902462637030e6439ca185b91c12d013efd205a041a09ef2da"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b5l9ds9sw6vy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$note = @\"\n\n## Iteration Economics Insight (23:55 ET)\nKey lesson: iteration frequency MATTERS more than idle time optimization for convergence-bound tasks.\n- If task needs N iterations and each pulse takes T seconds, total time = N * T (plus idle wait)\n- If cron fires every I seconds but pulse takes T seconds, effective iteration rate = max(1/T, 1/I)\n- 30-min cron with 30s pulse = 1800s/iteration, mostly wasted idle time\n- 1-min cron with 30s pulse = 60s/iteration, nearly optimal\n- 500k iterations at 30-min intervals = ~14,700 days\n- 500k iterations at 1-min intervals = ~347 days\n- At 30s intervals (theoretical floor): ~173 days\nPractical floor: ~35-40s per pulse (LLM call dominates), so 1-min cron is near-optimal.\n\nAlso: stateless discontinuous agents benefit MORE from fast iteration than continuous agents — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction, so iteration speed directly maps to learning/convergence speed.\n\nApplied: Sandbox-Pulse cron updated from 10min to 1min (id: d5964274-e7d4-4a4d-a6fb-59d1ce026dc0)\n\"@\n$note | Out-File -FilePath \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md\" -Append -Encoding UTF8\nWrite-Output \"Noted\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79229,"output":377,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324639651}}
{"type":"message","id":"889c6536","parentId":"5b304deb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:31.588Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b5l9ds9sw6vy_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Noted"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":711,"aggregated":"Noted","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324651557}}
{"type":"message","id":"166ae878","parentId":"889c6536","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:40.678Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Also let me write a dedicated note to the sandbox state/current_goals.md so it's part of the sandbox's own memory/context for when the agent runs.","thinkingSignature":"2b3759f25adf4136633abfab305866432b45aa6c1566d639b9594b10ceb83107"},{"type":"text","text":"Also writing it into the sandbox's own context so the agent sees it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tf5cvv53ew76_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$goalsFile = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md\"\nif (Test-Path $goalsFile) {\n    $current = Get-Content $goalsFile -Encoding UTF8 -Raw\n    $new_note = @\"\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\n\"@\n    $new_note | Out-File -FilePath $goalsFile -Append -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Output \"Appended to current_goals.md\"\n} else {\n    Write-Output \"Goals file not found\"\n}","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79624,"output":301,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93720,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324651590}}
