{"type":"message","id":"67ea5917","parentId":"ce6e7231","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:57:47.928Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Both done. Let me also note it in a more shareable format in case Zach wants to use it as a dataset example. I could write it to the workspace as a standalone note.\n\nActually, the memory file and the sandbox goals file are enough. Let me just confirm to Zach what I did.","thinkingSignature":"46a9dc36a612066e6592e6142cbba83818979448c6f806c273adb1ca943e9ad5"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. Cron is now 1 minute, and the insight is saved in two places:\n- `memory/2026-03-23.md` — for your own reference\n- `sandbox/state/current_goals.md` — so the sandbox agent itself can reason about iteration economics\n\nAlso worth noting for the dataset angle: the insight is general — any convergence-bound autonomous agent has this property. The discontinuity between iterations is pure waste when convergence speed is the bottleneck. It's a good framing for why stateless discontinuous agents need to be as fast as possible per iteration rather than just smart."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79948,"output":184,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93927,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774324661543}}
