{"type":"message","id":"1f5827d3","parentId":"83e6493b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:58:22.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sandbox is using `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku...` which is a coding plan subscription key. That's good - it's the right key. But wait, looking at the cron job payload, it specifies `MiniMax-M2.7` as the model. The coding plan might have different model options available. Let me check the cron job payload more carefully.\n\nActually, the cron job payload says `\"model\": \"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7\"`. But the API key in `.llm_key` is `sk-cp-...` which looks like an OpenAI key format, not a MiniMax key. \n\nSo either this is a unified key that works across both APIs, or the sandbox is actually routing through OpenAI's MiniMax integration rather than directly to MiniMax. The key format `sk-cp-` suggests it's an OpenAI-compatible key, which means the endpoint in `call_llm.py` is probably using OpenAI's base URL with MiniMax models, or there's a unified API gateway handling both. Let me check what `call_llm.py` is actually set up to use.","thinkingSignature":"980a62731a8b41ab298cee35b545d39a74caab2f49e2f6eed1057faadac47582"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_317rxln4mf8g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\call_llm.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80098,"output":296,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94189,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324694155}}
{"type":"message","id":"138549be","parentId":"1f5827d3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:58:22.319Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_317rxln4mf8g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nllm.py — clean LLM call wrapper for sandbox pulse\nCalls MiniMax-M2.7 API and writes response to .llm_response.txt\nPython subprocess avoids PowerShell heredoc/encoding issues.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\nRESPONSE_FILE = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_response.txt\")\n\ndef get_api_key():\n    with open(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_key\")) as f:\n        return f.read().strip()\n\ndef call_llm(prompt, model=\"MiniMax-M2.7\", max_tokens=1200):\n    api_key = get_api_key()\n    url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"\n    payload = {\"model\": model, \"max_tokens\": max_tokens, \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]}\n    data = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=data, headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n            result = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n            choices = result.get(\"choices\", [])\n            if choices:\n                content = choices[0].get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n                return content or \"\"\n            return \"\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return f\"HTTP_ERROR:{e.code}:{e.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace')}\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"ERROR:{type(e).__name__}:{str(e)}\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python llm.py <prompt_file>\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    with open(sys.argv[1], encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        prompt = f.read()\n    result = call_llm(prompt)\n    # Write to file to avoid Windows console encoding issues (Greek, emoji, etc.)\n    with open(RESPONSE_FILE, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        f.write(result)\n    # Also print to stderr for logging\n    print(f\"LLM response written to {RESPONSE_FILE}: {len(result)} chars\", file=sys.stderr)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324702274}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d8a6f45","parentId":"138549be","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:58:29.582Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `call_llm.py` is using:\n- API: `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions`\n- Model: `MiniMax-M2.7` (default)\n- Key: from `.llm_key` file\n\nThe key `sk-cp-boO3RF_...` looks like an OpenAI API key format, but it's being used with the MiniMax API. MiniMax's API actually accepts OpenAI-compatible key formats for their hosted models. So the setup is correct.\n\nThe cron job payload specifies `MiniMax-M2.7` via the model parameter, and the `call_llm.py` defaults to `MiniMax-M2.7`. \n\nEverything checks out—MiniMax M2.7 is running through the coding plan subscription key, so no changes needed.","thinkingSignature":"ad5ff6ff0abccbe441ae8a4aa9b6350bad74c321cca3d32d725882e3493d459e"},{"type":"text","text":"It's already correct:\n- Cron job payload uses `MiniMax-M2.7`\n- `call_llm.py` hits `api.minimax.io` and defaults to `MiniMax-M2.7`\n- `.llm_key` has your coding plan subscription key\n\nNothing to change — it's running the right model with the right key."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80932,"output":241,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94968,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774324702322}}
