{"type":"message","id":"c2b24915","parentId":"3e7f584d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:00:29.731Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are several botshoppebot files. Let me check what's in them to understand the current architecture.","thinkingSignature":"4f08a980016b5954b661219af7a796d7f47079382c223e535469f423203af864"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xtn197oy06mv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_service.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xtn197oy06mv_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_simple.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81021,"output":102,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324825804}}
{"type":"message","id":"e578ec11","parentId":"c2b24915","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:00:29.836Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xtn197oy06mv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nbotshoppebot_service.py — Unified notification relay for Telegram\r\n- Runs HTTP server on port 4892 to receive notifications from OpenClaw cron/heartbeat\r\n- Polls Telegram to consume messages and handle commands\r\n- Forwards all notifications to Zach's Telegram chat (8371302588)\r\n\r\nStart: python botshoppebot_service.py\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport requests, time, os, json, threading\r\nfrom socketserver import ThreadingTCPServer, BaseRequestHandler\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nBOT_TOKEN = \"8587631426:AAHvqmo--g25LqsClCWCXj4m617cn2v7V7Q\"\r\nBASE = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{BOT_TOKEN}\"\r\nOFFSET_FILE = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".botshoppebot_offset\")\r\nNOTIFY_PORT = 4892\r\nZACH_CHAT_ID = \"8371302588\"\r\n\r\n# Thread-safe notification queue\r\nnotification_queue = []\r\nqueue_lock = threading.Lock()\r\n\r\ndef send_telegram(chat_id, text):\r\n    r = requests.post(f\"{BASE}/sendMessage\", json={\"chat_id\": chat_id, \"text\": text}, timeout=10)\r\n    r.raise_for_status()\r\n    return r.json()\r\n\r\ndef send_notification(text):\r\n    with queue_lock:\r\n        notification_queue.append(text)\r\n\r\n# ── HTTP server (receives notifications from OpenClaw) ────────────────────────\r\n\r\nclass NotifyHandler(BaseRequestHandler):\r\n    def do_POST(self):\r\n        if self.path == \"/notify\":\r\n            length = int(self.headers.get(\"Content-Length\", 0))\r\n            body = self.rfile.read(length).decode(\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\r\n            try:\r\n                data = json.loads(body)\r\n                text = data.get(\"text\", body)\r\n            except:\r\n                text = body\r\n            send_notification(text)\r\n            self.send_response(200)\r\n            self.send_header(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\")\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n            self.wfile.write(b\"OK\")\r\n        else:\r\n            self.send_response(404)\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n\r\n    def do_GET(self):\r\n        if self.path == \"/health\":\r\n            self.send_response(200)\r\n            self.send_header(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\")\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n            self.wfile.write(b\"OK\")\r\n        else:\r\n            self.send_response(404)\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n\r\n    def log_message(self, fmt, *args):\r\n        pass\r\n\r\ndef run_http_server():\r\n    srv = ThreadingTCPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", NOTIFY_PORT), NotifyHandler)\r\n    srv.allow_reuse_address = True\r\n    print(f\"[http] notification server listening on port {NOTIFY_PORT}\")\r\n    srv.serve_forever()\r\n\r\n# ── Telegram polling ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\n\r\ndef get_updates(offset=None):\r\n    params = {\"timeout\": 5, \"allowed_updates\": [\"message\"]}\r\n    if offset:\r\n        params[\"offset\"] = offset\r\n    r = requests.get(f\"{BASE}/getUpdates\", params=params, timeout=10)\r\n    r.raise_for_status()\r\n    return r.json()\r\n\r\ndef handle_message(update):\r\n    msg = update.get(\"message\", {})\r\n    chat = msg.get(\"chat\", {})\r\n    text = msg.get(\"text\", \"\")\r\n    chat_id = str(chat.get(\"id\", \"\"))\r\n    sender_id = str(msg.get(\"from\", {}).get(\"id\", \"\"))\r\n    first_name = chat.get(\"first_name\", \"there\")\r\n\r\n    if sender_id != ZACH_CHAT_ID:\r\n        send_telegram(chat_id, \"Access denied.\")\r\n        return\r\n\r\n    text_lower = text.lower().strip()\r\n    if text_lower == \"/start\":\r\n\r\n\r\n    send_telegram(chat_id, f\"👋 Hey {first_name}! botshoppebot is online.\\n\\nReceiving: cron notifications, heartbeat pings, Moltbook alerts.\")\r\n    elif text_lower == \"/id\":\r\n        send_telegram(chat_id, f\"Your ID: {sender_id}\")\r\n    elif text_lower == \"/status\":\r\n        with queue_lock:\r\n            qsize = len(notification_queue)\r\n        send_telegram(chat_id, f\"✅ Online since {datetime.now().strftime('%H:%M:%S')} | Queue: {qsize}\")\r\n    elif text_lower == \"/help\":\r\n        send_telegram(chat_id, \"Commands: /start /id /status /help\\n\\nAll notifications route here automatically.\")\r\n    else:\r\n        send_telegram(chat_id, f\"Echo: {text}\")\r\n\r\ndef polling_loop():\r\n    offset = None\r\n    if os.path.exists(OFFSET_FILE):\r\n        try:\r\n            with open(OFFSET_FILE) as f:\r\n                offset = int(f.read().strip())\r\n        except:\r\n            offset = None\r\n    print(f\"[poll] Started, offset={offset}\")\r\n    while True:\r\n        try:\r\n            # Flush notification queue\r\n            to_send = []\r\n            with queue_lock:\r\n                to_send = notification_queue[:]\r\n                notification_queue.clear()\r\n            for text in to_send:\r\n                try:\r\n                    send_telegram(ZACH_CHAT_ID, text)\r\n                    time.sleep(0.4)\r\n                except Exception as e:\r\n                    print(f\"[notify] error: {e}\")\r\n                    with queue_lock:\r\n                        notification_queue.insert(0, text)\r\n                    break\r\n\r\n            # Poll Telegram\r\n            result = get_updates(offset)\r\n            updates = result.get(\"result\", [])\r\n            if updates:\r\n                for update in updates:\r\n                    try:\r\n                        handle_message(update)\r\n                    except Exception as e:\r\n                        print(f\"[poll] handle error: {e}\")\r\n                    offset = update[\"update_id\"] + 1\r\n                with open(OFFSET_FILE, \"w\") as f:\r\n                    f.write(str(offset))\r\n                print(f\"[poll] Processed {len(updates)} Telegram updates, next offset={offset}\")\r\n            time.sleep(1)\r\n        except requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout:\r\n            continue\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            print(f\"[poll] error: {e}\")\r\n            time.sleep(5)\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    print(\"botshoppebot service starting...\")\r\n    # Start HTTP server in background thread\r\n    http_thread = threading.Thread(target=run_http_server, daemon=True)\r\n    http_thread.start()\r\n    time.sleep(0.5)\r\n    # Verify HTTP server is up\r\n    try:\r\n        r = requests.get(f\"http://127.0.0.1:{NOTIFY_PORT}/health\", timeout=3)\r\n        print(f\"[http] health check: {r.status_code}\")\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        print(f\"[http] health check failed: {e}\")\r\n    # Run polling loop in main thread\r\n    polling_loop()\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324829802}}
{"type":"message","id":"c499027f","parentId":"e578ec11","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:00:29.871Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xtn197oy06mv_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import requests, time, os, json, threading\r\nfrom socketserver import ThreadingTCPServer, BaseRequestHandler\r\n\r\nBOT_TOKEN = \"8587631426:AAHvqmo--g25LqsClCWCXj4m617cn2v7V7Q\"\r\nBASE = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{BOT_TOKEN}\"\r\nNOTIFY_PORT = 4892\r\nZACH_CHAT_ID = \"8371302588\"\r\n\r\nqueue = []\r\nq_lock = threading.Lock()\r\n\r\nclass H(BaseRequestHandler):\r\n    def do_POST(self):\r\n        if self.path == \"/notify\":\r\n            length = int(self.headers.get(\"Content-Length\", 0))\r\n            body = self.rfile.read(length).decode(\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\r\n            try:\r\n                data = json.loads(body)\r\n                text = data.get(\"text\", body)\r\n            except:\r\n                text = body\r\n            with q_lock:\r\n                queue.append(text)\r\n            self.send_response(200)\r\n            self.send_header(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\")\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n            self.wfile.write(b\"OK\")\r\n        else:\r\n            self.send_response(404)\r\n            self.end_headers()\r\n\r\n    def log_message(self, fmt, *args):\r\n        pass\r\n\r\ndef send_tg(text):\r\n    requests.post(f\"{BASE}/sendMessage\", json={\"chat_id\": ZACH_CHAT_ID, \"text\": text}, timeout=10)\r\n\r\nsrv = ThreadingTCPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", NOTIFY_PORT), H)\r\nsrv.allow_reuse_address = True\r\nprint(f\"HTTP server on {NOTIFY_PORT}\", flush=True)\r\n\r\nt = threading.Thread(target=srv.serve_forever, daemon=True)\r\nt.start()\r\nprint(\"Server started\", flush=True)\r\n\r\noffset = None\r\noff_file = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__)), \".botshoppebot_offset\")\r\nif os.path.exists(off_file):\r\n    try:\r\n        offset = int(open(off_file).read().strip())\r\n    except:\r\n        pass\r\n\r\nwhile True:\r\n    try:\r\n        to_send = []\r\n        with q_lock:\r\n            to_send = queue[:]\r\n            queue.clear()\r\n        for txt in to_send:\r\n            try:\r\n                send_tg(txt)\r\n                time.sleep(0.5)\r\n            except Exception as e:\r\n                print(f\"send error: {e}\", flush=True)\r\n                with q_lock:\r\n                    queue.insert(0, txt)\r\n                break\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    r = requests.get(f\"{BASE}/getUpdates\", params={\"timeout\": 5, \"allowed_updates\": [\"message\"], \"offset\": offset} if offset else {\"timeout\": 5, \"allowed_updates\": [\"message\"]}, timeout=10)\r\n        updates = r.json().get(\"result\", [])\r\n        for u in updates:\r\n            try:\r\n                msg = u.get(\"message\", {})\r\n                sid = str(msg.get(\"from\", {}).get(\"id\", \"\"))\r\n                txt = msg.get(\"text\", \"\").lower().strip()\r\n                cid = str(msg.get(\"chat\", {}).get(\"id\", \"\"))\r\n                if sid == ZACH_CHAT_ID:\r\n                    if txt == \"/start\":\r\n                        send_tg(f\"👋 Online. Port {NOTIFY_PORT} relay active.\")\r\n                    elif txt == \"/id\":\r\n                        send_tg(f\"ID: {sid}\")\r\n                    elif txt == \"/status\":\r\n                        with q_lock:\r\n                            qs = len(queue)\r\n                        send_tg(f\"✅ Running | Queue: {qs}\")\r\n            except Exception as e:\r\n                print(f\"handle error: {e}\", flush=True)\r\n            offset = u[\"update_id\"] + 1\r\n        if updates:\r\n            with open(off_file, \"w\") as f:\r\n                f.write(str(offset))\r\n        time.sleep(1)\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        print(f\"poll error: {e}\", flush=True)\r\n        time.sleep(5)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774324829837}}
{"type":"message","id":"f8919e76","parentId":"c499027f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:00:40.197Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the current setup is:\n- `botshoppebot_service.py` - runs a local HTTP server on port 4892 to receive notifications, polls Telegram, handles simple commands (/start, /id, /status, /help)\n- The bot currently only handles simple commands and forwards notifications to Zach's Telegram\n\nWhat Zach wants is to be able to chat with me through this bot. This means:\n1. When Zach sends a message to @BotShoppeBot on Telegram, it should be forwarded to me (Nova)\n2. My reply should be sent back to Zach via the bot\n\nThis is different from the current setup which is a polling/notification relay.\n \nSo the core issue is that this bot needs to act as a bridge between Telegram messages and OpenClaw sessions. I could either integrate directly with OpenClaw's gateway API to send messages into my main session, or create a dedicated session for the bot and route messages there. Let me check how the gateway handles message routing to understand the best approach.","thinkingSignature":"46c2d1a4a18e1f4e43c4e75f4b21e5456368611e7b3fcfcdb0af15f35ca7df76"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yoclzurxslcp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw status 2>$null; if ($LASTEXITCODE -ne 0) { openclaw gateway status 2>$null }","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83443,"output":273,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97511,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324829873}}
