{"type":"message","id":"e18a7a53","parentId":"3f83083c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:01:15.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! So OpenClaw has a Telegram plugin configured with a different bot token (`7669304147:AAHVFq38PYGmS_Shc7bCxtMLUXyKE4_k6cU`). This is a different bot from @BotShoppeBot (`8587631426:AAHvqmo--g25LqsClCWCXj4m617cn2v7V7Q`). The bot token `7669304147:AAHVFq38PYGmS_Shc7bCxtMLUXyKE4_k6cU` is likely @hedgehogclawbot (which was mentioned as the other working bot).\nThe real issue is that OpenClaw's Telegram plugin is already bound to @hedgehogclawbot, so if I want @BotShoppeBot to work with OpenClaw, I'd need to either swap out the plugin's token or add @BotShoppeBot as a second bot—which OpenClaw doesn't seem to support yet. I need to figure out whether OpenClaw's Telegram plugin can only handle one bot at a time, or if there's a way to configure it to use the @BotShoppeBot token instead. The plugin might support it through something like a `botToken` field, but I'd need to check the config format to be sure. Alternatively, I could build a bridge that forwards messages from @BotShoppeBot to my OpenClaw session.","thinkingSignature":"988e6166d45404f4981c64596226eb8fcc7b9be95ab32d731e78464eea20f20a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6bgjo5zjdl16_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json","offset":240,"limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85393,"output":356,"cacheRead":13795,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99544,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774324866455}}
