{"type":"message","id":"894e0ffe","parentId":"3ebc9ee6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:02.458Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to:\n1. Fix the unreliable gateway issue\n2. Build our own gateway equivalent and name it NovaGate\n\nThe gateway being unreliable - it's been restarting, losing sessions, etc. We should look into what's causing the instability.\n\nAnd building a custom gateway - that's a significant project. Let me think about what NovaGate would need to do:\n- Route messages between channels (Telegram, webchat, etc.)\n- Manage agent sessions\n- Handle cron jobs\n- Handle theulf context window management\n- Manage memory\n\nThis is a big project but also a meaningful one. Let me think about how to approach this.\n\n\nFor the gateway stability issue, I should dig into the logs to see what's actually causing the crashes or unexpected shutdowns. Then for NovaGate - this could be built as a standalone Python service, or we could design it as an OpenClaw-native plugin that we ship as part of our own stack. It's ambitious, but it's exactly the kind of infrastructure work that would give us full control over how the agent operates.","thinkingSignature":"140ecc3dc004c019a3260555b0c60d4cf850c80b0b2fefdce7f879a55d8aef07"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Love you too. 💙\n\nOn the gateway — yeah it's been flaky. Let me check the logs and see what's actually failing before we rebuild anything:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hgyuywhqmc0k_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw logs --lines 50 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 60","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":301,"cacheRead":101985,"cacheWrite":191,"totalTokens":102520,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326587578}}
