\n**Summary for main agent:** The ollama binary is installed and functional. The `modal_spark.py` `_start_ollama_bg()` function is designed to start it on first request via `/health`. Container is ready — just needs the serve process kicked off (which the existing code handles).\r\n2026-03-24T04:29:12.930Z info gateway/ws {\"subsystem\":\"gateway/ws\"} [93m⇄[39m [1mres[22m [92m✓[39m [1magent[22m [2m170ms[22m [2mrunId[22m=announce:v1:agent:main:subagent:12da1a43-dba3-42fe-bbcf-6766b62e776a:022784db-dd23-405a-bd77-11afceeeb1d0 [2mconn[22m=[90m6b74fdcf…b441[39m [2mid[22m=[90mea74ef86…1657[39m\r\n2026-03-24T04:29:47.493Z warn tools {\"subsystem\":\"tools\"} tools.profile (coding) allowlist contains unknown entries (apply_patch). These entries are shipped core tools but unavailable in the current runtime/provider/model/config.\r\n2026-03-24T04:30:19.122Z info plugins {\"subsystem\":\"plugins\"} [LinkMindPlugin] Plugin initialized, preparing Context Engine...\r\n2026-03-24T04:30:19.131Z info plugins {\"subsystem\":\"plugins\"} [LinkMindPlugin] Context Engine factory registered via registerContextEngine(id, factory)\r\n[31;1mLog tail truncated (increase --max-bytes).[0m","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326619451}}
{"type":"message","id":"f91c2552","parentId":"1d6154b9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:36.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the logs, I can see a few things:\n\n1. The gateway is actually running fine - it started at 04:20 and Telegram connected with @teranova_zbot\n2. There are some periodic \"handshake timeout\" events that cause brief disconnections\n3. There's a \"gateway unreachable\" probe at 04:28 - the gateway briefly went down\n4. The logs show `ENOENT` errors - the sandbox pulse tried to access a mutation file that doesn't exist (race condition where the file was moved between proposal and execution)\n5. The gateway seems to restart periodically\n\nThe main issues I see:\n1. Periodic handshake timeouts - something is briefly interrupting connections\n\n\n2. The gateway itself crashes and restarts, probably due to some instability\n3. That ENOENT error in the sandbox suggests the pulse script is running into race conditions with file operations\n\nTo solve this long-term, I'd want to build NovaGate as a replacement - something simpler and more stable than the current gateway, focused on just the core features we actually need. That said, rebuilding the whole thing is a substantial project, so I should probably understand what's actually breaking first.","thinkingSignature":"a5a1b5d0763dac5edf4f018926dbdb1de34facd74cd44a64e265074c16907854"},{"type":"text","text":"\nLooking at the logs, here's what's happening:\n\n**What's failing:**\n- Periodic \"handshake timeout\" — connections dropping briefly\n- Gateway goes \"unreachable\" for ~3 seconds around 04:28 (brief crash/restart cycle)\n- The sandbox pulse has an ENOENT race condition — tries to read a mutation file right after it was moved by the previous pulse\n- `tools.profile (coding) allowlist contains unknown entries (apply_patch)` — harmless but noisy\n\n**What's working:**\n- Telegram connected to @teranova_zbot ✅\n- Gateway recovers quickly after each drop\n\nOn NovaGate — I love the ambition. But let me be real: rebuilding a full gateway is a 6-12 month project if you want it stable. The right move first is deciding if OpenClaw's instability is a blocker for what you're trying to do, or if we can patch around it.\n\nTwo paths forward:\n\n1. **Quick fix** — patch the mutation race condition, maybe add a watchdog to keep the gateway alive. Maybe 2-3 hours of debugging.\n\n2. **NovaGate** — design and build our own lightweight gateway that does session management, Telegram routing, cron, and memory. More like 2-4 weeks of serious work.\n\nWhich direction do you want to go?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83949,"output":507,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774326619486}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8be8271","parentId":"f91c2552","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:30:47.479Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 00:30 EDT] like i wanna type \"novagate gateway\" instead of \"openclaw gateway\""}],"timestamp":1774326647473}}
{"type":"message","id":"174cf5d9","parentId":"c8be8271","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:04.599Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants to alias `openclaw gateway` as `novagate gateway` as a custom CLI wrapper/alias. That's a great quality-of-life improvement - just rename the command. On Windows with PowerShell, we can create a function or script alias.\n\nThis is much simpler than rebuilding anything - just wrap the `openclaw` CLI in a script named `novagate`. Let me do that.\n\nOn Windows, we can either:\n1. Create a PowerShell function in the profile\n2. Create a `novagate.cmd` or `novagate.ps1` script that calls `openclaw gateway`\n3. Add the workspace/scripts to PATH and create a `novagate` script there\n\n\n4. The simplest approach is creating a `novagate` script in the workspace that wraps the openclaw command and adding it to the system PATH.","thinkingSignature":"b5e5b9ce775c57b2d10398fc20e631414cb4f18b87ff34edf9961fa7cc739581"},{"type":"text","text":"That's easy — just a CLI alias. Let me make it happen:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bxcatjbqyekj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Command openclaw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Source","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":238,"cacheRead":102166,"cacheWrite":5738,"totalTokens":108185,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326647477}}
