{"type":"message","id":"2193f5fa","parentId":"da2d3c64","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:10.377Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So openclaw is actually a `.ps1` file in the npm global path. I can create a `novagate.ps1` wrapper in the same directory, or better yet in the workspace and add it to PATH.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach on Windows: create `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\novagate.cmd` that just forwards to openclaw. Or a `novagate.ps1` in the same dir.\n\nLet me create a simple wrapper:","thinkingSignature":"ec14942a6b9843381ff3845e99313f5997683411546e21e80e7845ed355c9b93"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8cea3qxnbb9_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\novagate.cmd","content":"@echo off\nnode \"%~dp0openclaw.js\" %*\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94347,"output":167,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108385,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326665503}}
