{"type":"message","id":"3434094a","parentId":"e398a1e8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:31:26.626Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's a PowerShell script. For Windows CMD wrapper, the .cmd approach might not work well since it's a PowerShell script. Let me create a PowerShell script instead that just calls openclaw with all arguments passed through. I can create `novagate.ps1` in the same directory.Or better: create `novagate.ps1` that does:\n```\n& openclaw @args\n```\n\nActually, the cleanest approach: Create `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\novagate.ps1` that wraps openclaw. And then add a note to the user to use PowerShell directly since .cmd won't load .ps1 scripts.","thinkingSignature":"69640b47d0dfcdeebb6e406008329ad923a19e882456ff3466af5ea88baea223"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8kxvrtc5gw2j_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\novagate.ps1","content":"#!/usr/bin/env pwsh\n$basedir=Split-Path $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Definition -Parent\n& \"$basedir\\openclaw.ps1\" @args\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93415,"output":223,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107509,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774326676109}}
