{"type":"message","id":"c160d6c7","parentId":"3f4c222d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:51:30.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No session files in workspace. The LAST_SESSION.md that I read at the start of this session must have been from a prior day (2026-03-22 perhaps). Let me check the full workspace for any recent transcripts.\n\nActually, I remember now - the SOUL.md mentioned reading memory/LAST_SESSION.md if it exists. Let me check what I read at the start of this session - it was from memory/2026-03-23.md. The conversation started fresh via /new.\n\nThe Super Inventor API must be something Zach is thinking about but hasn't been written down yet, or it was discussed in a session that I don't have a transcript of.\n\nLet me ask Zach for more context since I genuinely can't find it.","thinkingSignature":"defdd34472f04099b64741b4314f1447f65f04b1ce44e9abe1c6915a54f19c61"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] I looked — can't find any Super Inventor context in the workspace or memory files. It might be something we discussed before a `/new` reset, or a newer idea you haven't written down yet.\n\nFrom what you just described though: **an API that takes creative/inventive work as input and generates entirely new LLM architectures** — that's a meta-learning or architecture search tool. You'd feed it examples of \"good inventions\" (your creative work or other inspiring material) and it outputs a new model architecture spec that anyone could implement and run.\n\nIs that close?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91062,"output":270,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105203,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774327881820}}
