{"type":"message","id":"d096d0a7","parentId":"985f177f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:36:27.378Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me create the SPEC for the Super Inventor API and also set up the directory structure. I'll write a proper SPEC.md document that captures:\n1. The dream\n2. What it does\n3. The architecture\n4. The API spec\n5. The build pipeline\n6. A notes section for the minimal UI\n\nLet me think about what this should contain carefully.\n\nThe Super Inventor API:\n- Takes creative/inventive input (research notes, architecture ideas, what worked in infant/mind/COG/SR-MoE)\n- Uses an LLM to synthesize this into new architecture specifications\n- Outputs implementable configs (YAML/JSON) that can be fed to a build pipeline\n\n\n- Operates entirely on CPU with no GPU or cloud dependencies\n- Can also propose experiments to validate architecture ideas\n\nFor the web UI, I need a simple interface where Zach can input ideas and see the generated architecture specs, with me interpreting and explaining the results. Since I'm Nova, I'll be the intermediary—Zach communicates in natural language, I handle the API calls and feedback loop, and we use a lightweight frontend just for visibility into what's happening.\n\nLet me start by drafting the SPEC document.","thinkingSignature":"294be8f5ecb059e60b4984e6068fd9833c5de4dd30efb6c9cfd2a526ffbc5642"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m9kmj2ugu3mk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path \"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\" | Out-Null; Write-Output \"Created\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30,"output":307,"cacheRead":105539,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105876,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774330573376}}
