{"type":"message","id":"9a14c5c4","parentId":"95d399d4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:37:32.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the SPEC. I need to think carefully about what this should contain.The Super Inventor API:1. **Purpose**: Take creative/inventive input from Zach, synthesize it with existing architecture research into new LLM architecture specs2. **Key constraint**: No GPU, no cloud. Must produce architectures that run on CPU\n3. **Architecture types**: SR-MoE (sparse routing), infant cognitive architecture, temporal attention, etc.4. **Output**: YAML/JSON model configs that can be built with a simple Python inference engine\n5. **Pipeline**: Zach → Nova → SuperInventorAPI → spec files → build → test\n\n\n6. **The minimal UI**: Just a clean web interface that shows the conversation between Zach and Nova, displays the generated spec, and allows Zach to approve/reject/modify. Nova is the translator.\n\nFor the technical implementation, I'm thinking Zach talks to me in natural language about architecture ideas, I translate that into API calls to the SuperInventor backend, which synthesizes new architecture specs using the existing research and outputs YAML configs. The build pipeline then takes those specs and constructs a runnable model.\n\nNow I need to nail down the actual API spec itself. The core endpoint takes the creative input and research context, returns an architecture spec with name, parameters, config YAML, reasoning, and suggested experiments. Then there's a secondary endpoint for generating test datasets to validate whether the architecture actually works as intended.\n\nFor the frontend, I'm keeping it minimal—just a chat-like interface where Zach can post ideas, see the generated specs, and iterate on them. The build endpoint just takes the spec YAML and confirms whether the build succeeds or fails, with Nova handling error interpretation if something breaks.\n\nThis is ambitious but I should draft it carefully since Zach is trusting me to get the architecture right.","thinkingSignature":"73a6e18f1ceedb02fabf34dd0bc3e229c7978df834b4bb6eec19b1f7f6e99aa2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_utucifmivw04_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\SPEC.md","content":"# Super Inventor API — SPEC\n\n_Created: 2026-03-24_\n\n---\n\n## The Dream\n\nAn API that transforms inventive ideas into new types of AI that anyone can run on a laptop — no GPU, no cloud, no corporate dependency. Free, private, uncensored, competitive with the giants.\n\nThe vision: Zach talks to Nova about architecture ideas, intuitions, things that worked in infant/mind/COG/SR-MoE research. Nova translates that into Super Inventor API calls. The API synthesizes the inventive input with architecture research into working model specs. Zach builds and tests. We iterate together.\n\n**The goal is not incremental improvement. It's inventing a new type of AI.**\n\n---\n\n## Core Insight\n\nMost LLM inefficiency comes from activating the entire model for every token. The solution is sparse activation — only the parts that matter fire. SR-MoE is already pointing here (sparse routing mixture-of-experts with a ring attractor). This is the thread to pull.\n\nAdditional threads to weave in:\n- Infant's dual-head architecture (frozen core + flexible learning)\n- Temporal attention's focus decay (memory without memory overhead)\n- Cognitive reflex loops from mind-agent\n\n---\n\n## API Specification\n\n### Base URL\n`http://localhost:4891` (local server, no cloud)\n\n### Endpoints\n\n#### `POST /invent`\nTake inventive input and synthesize a new architecture specification.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"idea\": \"string — raw inventive idea in plain language\",\n  \"context\": {\n    \"existing_architectures\": [\"sr-moe\", \"infant\", \"temporal-attention\", \"mind\"],\n    \"constraints\": {\n      \"no_gpu\": true,\n      \"no_cloud\": true,\n      \"target\": \"consumer_cpu\",\n      \"max_params\": 7000000000,\n      \"max_ram_gb\": 16\n    },\n    \"inspiration\": \"string — optionally, specific examples that worked\"\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"creative | conservative\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"architecture\": {\n    \"name\": \"string — generated architecture name\",\n    \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n    \"core_idea\": \"string — one sentence of what makes it novel\",\n    \"yaml\": \"string — complete model config YAML\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"string — detailed explanation of design choices\",\n    \"novelty_score\": 0.0-1.0,\n    \"expected_strengths\": [\"string\"],\n    \"expected_weaknesses\": [\"string\"]\n  },\n  \"experiments\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"string\",\n      \"hypothesis\": \"string\",\n      \"success_metric\": \"string\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"build_commands\": [\"string — shell commands to build/test\"],\n  \"warnings\": [\"string — things that might not work\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### `POST /build`\nTake a generated architecture YAML and attempt to build it.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"yaml\": \"string — architecture config YAML from /invent\"\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"build_output\": \"string — raw build log\",\n  \"model_loaded\": true,\n  \"inference_test\": {\n    \"passed\": true,\n    \"output\": \"string — sample model output\",\n    \"latency_ms\": 0\n  },\n  \"errors\": [\"string — if any\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### `POST /test`\nRun a defined experiment against a built architecture.\n\n**Request:**\n```json\n{\n  \"architecture_name\": \"string\",\n  \"experiment\": {\n    \"name\": \"string\",\n    \"dataset\": \"string — path or name\",\n    \"iterations\": 1000,\n    \"metrics\": [\"accuracy\", \"latency\", \"memory_usage\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"results\": {\n    \"metric_name\": {\n      \"value\": 0.0,\n      \"expected\": 0.0,\n      \"delta\": 0.0\n    }\n  },\n  \"verdict\": \"pass | partial | fail\",\n  \"recommendations\": [\"string\"]\n}\n```\n\n#### `GET /architectures`\nList all architectures generated so far.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"architectures\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"string\",\n      \"version\": \"string\",\n      \"created_at\": \"ISO timestamp\",\n      \"status\": \"invented | built | tested | abandoned\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n#### `GET /architectures/<name>`\nGet full details of a specific architecture.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture YAML Format\n\nEvery generated architecture should output a standard YAML format that the build system can consume:\n\n```yaml\nname: <architecture_name>\nversion: 0.1.0\n\nmodel:\n  type: <core model type — e.g. srmoe, gru-attention, transformer variant>\n  hidden_dim: <int>\n  num_layers: <int>\n  vocab_size: <int>\n  max_seq_len: <int>\n\nsparsity:\n  mechanism: <sparse-routing | mixture-of-experts | attention-masking | other>\n  active_fraction: 0.0-1.0\n  cold_params: <int — params that never activate>\n\nmemory:\n  type: <none | external | associative | temporal>\n  max_memory_items: <int>\n  retrieval: <attention | cosine | both>\n\nrouting:\n  type: <gumbel-softmax | vq-codebook | ring-attractor | learned-projection>\n  num_codes: <int>\n  tau_start: <float>\n  tau_end: <float>\n\ninference:\n  device: cpu\n  quantize: <none | int8 | int4>\n  compile: <none | torch-compile>\n\ntraining:\n  device: gpu  # training can use GPU, inference must not\n  epochs: <int>\n  batch_size: <int>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Nova as Translator\n\nNova is the interface between Zach and the API.\n\nZach talks → Nova translates → API synthesizes → Nova interprets → Zach approves/revises\n\nNova's role:\n1. **Understand Zach's inventive ideas** — extract the core insight from natural language\n2. **Query the right context** — know which existing architectures (infant, mind, SR-MoE, temporal-attention) to reference\n3. **Call the API** — build the right request payload\n4. **Interpret the output** — explain what the generated architecture actually is in plain language\n5. **Manage the iteration** — if the build fails or test fails, Nova helps diagnose and reformulate\n\n---\n\n## Web UI — Minimal\n\nA single-page web app for visibility. Nova is the real interface.\n\n**Purpose:** See what's being sent, see what comes back, see build status. Not for typing — Zach talks to Nova directly.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Super Inventor                         Nova │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                             │\n│  [Chat log — Zach ↔ Nova conversation]      │\n│                                             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Current Architecture: <name>                │\n│  Status: invented | built | tested          │\n│  YAML preview (collapsible)                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Build Log:                                 │\n│  > building model...                        │\n│  > loading weights...                       │\n│  > inference test passed (42ms)             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Stack:** Simple Flask + vanilla HTML/JS. No framework needed.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1 — API Foundation\n- [ ] Flask server skeleton with all 5 endpoints\n- [ ] YAML schema validation\n- [ ] Architecture storage (JSON file, not database)\n- [ ] Basic LLM integration (MiniMax to start, self-hosted later)\n\n### Phase 2 — Core Synthesis\n- [ ] `/invent` prompt engineering — wire in infant, mind, SR-MoE, temporal-attention as context\n- [ ] `/build` — stub that always returns success, real build pipeline later\n- [ ] `/test` — stub\n- [ ] Nova translation layer\n\n### Phase 3 — Build Pipeline\n- [ ] Real build from YAML (Python model code generation)\n- [ ] CPU inference with quantization\n- [ ] Memory + latency benchmarking\n- [ ] Integration with `/build` endpoint\n\n### Phase 4 — UI + Iteration\n- [ ] Minimal Flask + HTML/JS UI\n- [ ] Real iteration loop: invent → build → test → revise\n- [ ] Zach testing with real hardware\n\n### Phase 5 — Self-Hosting\n- [ ] Remove MiniMax dependency\n- [ ] Route through self-hosted inference (EXP/KVict direction)\n- [ ] Full CPU-only operation\n\n---\n\n## Status\n\n**Phase 1** — Not started.\n**First step:** Create Flask server skeleton. Get the 5 endpoints returning structured responses.\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":92022,"output":2286,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774330588128}}
