{"type":"message","id":"1ccd37e5","parentId":"c50be094","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:45:31.789Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Phase 1 is done. Let me update the SPEC to mark Phase 1 as complete.","thinkingSignature":"9dc07e41f49d3d534ecc809c490c04a2dfd9dfcbf9ef6ae5c9ec8dfeb48762c3"},{"type":"text","text":"Phase 1 is done. Here's what we have:\n\n**`C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\`** — live on `http://localhost:4891`\n\n| Endpoint | Status |\n|----------|--------|\n| `POST /invent` | ✅ Returns architecture YAML |\n| `POST /build` | ✅ Validates YAML, returns stub |\n| `POST /test` | ✅ Returns stub results |\n| `GET /architectures` | ✅ Lists all generated |\n| `GET /architectures/<name>` | ✅ Returns full details |\n| `GET /health` | ✅ |\n\n**Next phases:**\n- **Phase 2** — Wire in the LLM for real synthesis. Nova reads the existing architectures (SR-MoE, infant, mind, temporal-attention) and the API calls MiniMax to turn ideas into real YAML specs.\n- **Phase 3** — Real build pipeline from YAML to actual model code.\n- **Phase 4** — Minimal web UI.\n\nServer is running. Want me to move to Phase 2 (LLM synthesis)?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83434,"output":238,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":97543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774331123742}}
