{"type":"message","id":"3610c3c7","parentId":"59da6e93","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:15:48.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to move to Phase 2 — wiring in the LLM for real synthesis. The API should call MiniMax to turn inventive ideas into real YAML architecture specs.\n\nI need to:\n1. Create an LLM call module for the SuperInventor API\n2. Modify the `/invent` endpoint to actually call the LLM with context from existing architectures\n3. Wire in the research from SR-MoE, infant, mind, temporal-attention\n\nLet me plan the LLM synthesis prompt carefully. The goal is to take an inventive idea and generate a novel, CPU-runnable LLM architecture YAML based on:\n\n\n- The core constraints (no GPU, no cloud, consumer CPU, max 7B params)\n- Inspiration from existing architectures (SR-MoE's sparse routing, infant's dual-head approach, temporal-attention's focus decay, mind-agent's cognitive reflexes)\n- The creativity of the idea itself\n\nI should read the key files from these existing architectures to understand what makes them work, then build that understanding into the synthesis prompt.","thinkingSignature":"7c249620fe0d9b7f75dc558b2eb3bf55c181525f76d4c28532aee74e09c9e3e5"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me first read the key research from the existing architectures to wire in as context:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s4nj3kf7l2wb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\dev\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Get-ChildItem \"C:\\dev\\infant\\README.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Get-ChildItem \"C:\\dev\\temporal-attention\\README.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Get-ChildItem \"C:\\dev\\mind\\README.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":353,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":105799,"totalTokens":110441,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead