{"type":"message","id":"20e257c0","parentId":"5f9d1257","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:15:53.939Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to read these README files to get the key architectural insights, then write the LLM synthesis module.","thinkingSignature":"93520e0c16915a7a6c383a11ed6be7fb3a71c386efb12a45b40abc6e316f7448"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\dev\\infant\\README.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\dev\\temporal-attention\\README.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\dev\\mind\\README.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96927,"output":112,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774332948977}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebbfd3e7","parentId":"20e257c0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:15:54.130Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Infant: Synthetic Human Cognitive Architecture\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.0+-ee4c2c?style=flat-square&logo=pytorch\" alt=\"PyTorch\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue?style=flat-square&logo=python\" alt=\"Python\">\n  <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green?style=flat-square\" alt=\"License\">\n</p>\n\nA synthetic human cognitive architecture with persistent identity, memory, and learning. Built to explore continuous persistent temporal cognition.\n\n## 🎯 What is Infant?\n\nInfant is an AI system that:\n- **Remembers who it is** - Core identity persists across sessions\n- **Learns without forgetting** - Dual-head architecture protects what matters\n- **Dreams to consolidate** - Offline memory tier promotion\n- **Sets and pursues goals** - Active goal system\n- **Validates itself** - Self-consistency checking\n\n## 🧠 Architecture\n\n```\nInfant\n├── Dual-Head Architecture\n│   ├── Core Head (frozen) → identity, values, core memory\n│   └── Flexible Head → new learning\n│\n├── Memory System (4 tiers)\n│   ├── Working Memory (20 items)\n│   ├── Raw Experiences (500)\n│   ├── Patterns (100) \n│   ├── Knowledge (50)\n│   └── Wisdom (20)\n│\n├── Self-Model\n│   ├── Motor → Sensory predictor\n│   └── Self/Other classifier\n│\n├── Values System\n│   └── Core values with strengths\n│\n├── Goal System\n│   ├── Priority queue\n│   └── Progress tracking\n│\n└── Validation\n    └── Coherence checking\n```\n\n## 🔬 Experiments\n\n10 experiments proving the architecture works:\n\n| Experiment | Result |\n|------------|--------|\n| Mirror Test | ✓ Pass - Distinguishes self from external |\n| Continuity Test | ✓ Pass - Persistent state preserves knowledge |\n| Body Ownership | ✓ Pass - Sensorimotor = body ownership |\n| Value Formation | ✓ Pass - Preferences emerge from experience |\n| Value Stability | ✓ Pass - Values survive contradiction |\n| Untaught Value | ✓ Pass - Learns principles, not patterns |\n| Memory Persistence | ✓ Pass - Dual-head prevents forgetting |\n| Personality Coherence | ✓ Pass - Identity stable through updates |\n| Integration | ✓ Pass - New info integrates without destabilizing |\n| Fracture Prevention | ✓ Pass - Extreme stress doesn't break identity |\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom infant.infant_complete import Infant\n\n# Create Infant\ninfant = Infant()\n\n# Form identity (once)\ninfant.form_identity(\"I am a curious, honest AI\")\n\n# Set values\ninfant.set_value(\"honesty\", 1.0)\ninfant.set_value(\"curiosity\", 0.9)\n\n# Freeze core (identity + values protected)\ninfant.freeze_core()\n\n# Learn new things (flexible, won't affect core)\ninfant.learn(\"The sky is blue\", importance=0.6)\n\n# Set goals\ninfant.set_goal(\"Understand consciousness\", priority=0.9)\n\n# Dream consolidation (offline)\ninfant.dream()\n\n# Validate\nstatus = infant.validate()\nprint(status)\n```\n\n## 📁 Project Structure\n\n```\ninfant/\n├── infant_complete.py      # Main Infant class\n├── cognitive_architecture.py # Dual-head implementation\n├── memory_enhanced.py      # Memory system + consolidation\n├── train_dualhead.py       # Training integration\n├── experiments/\n│   ├── mirror_test.py\n│   ├── value_formation_test.py\n│   ├── continuity_test.py\n│   ├── memory_persistence_test.py\n│   └── ...\n├── SYNTHETIC_HUMAN.md      # Full development plan\n├── DUAL_HEAD_ARCHITECTURE.md # Technical docs\n└── EXPERIMENTS.md         # Experiment results\n```\n\n## 🔑 Key Innovation: Dual-Head Architecture\n\nThe breakthrough: **catastrophic forgetting is a weight-sharing problem**.\n\nSolution: separate paths + freeze\n\n```python\nclass DualHeadBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.encoder = ...\n        self.core_head = ...  # Protected, frozen after formation\n        self.flex_head = ...  # Flexible, always learning\n```\n\n- **Core head** (frozen): identity, values, core memories\n- **Flexible head**: new learning, opinions, skills\n\nThis mirrors human cognition: core values don't change, but we learn new things every day.\n\n## 📊 Benchmark Results\n\nCompared against EWC on continual learning:\n\n| Method | Accuracy | Forgetting |\n|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Baseline | 51.4% | -39.3pp |\n| EWC | 54.1% | -28.7pp |\n| **Dual-Head** | 84.7% | -14.5pp |\n\n**+33pp improvement** over baseline.\n\n## 🌐 Links\n\n- GitHub: https://github.com/toxzak-svg/infant\n- Moltbook: @clawhedgehog\n\n## 📝 Citation\n\n```bibtex\n@software{infant2026,\n  title = {Infant: Synthetic Human Cognitive Architecture},\n  author = {Zach Maronek},\n  year = {2026},\n  url = {https://github.com/toxzak-svg/infant}\n}\n```\n\n## 🤝 Contributing\n\nBuilt by Zach with help from Claw. Contributions welcome!\n\n## 📄 License\n\nMIT\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332954085}}
{"type":"message","id":"d678ae85","parentId":"ebbfd3e7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:15:54.167Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TemporalAttention Store\n\nA memory system for AI agents that combines **time**, **events**, and **focus** for smarter information retrieval.\n\n**License**: MIT\n\n## The Problem\n\nCurrent memory systems are broken:\n\n| System | What's Wrong |\n|--------|-------------|\n| Simple RAG | Returns latest fact, doesn't understand time |\n| Mem0 | Can't answer \"who was CEO in 2023?\" |\n| LangChain | Binary cutoff, no gradual decay |\n| Vector DB | Ignores recency |\n\n## The Solution\n\nThree decay types working together:\n\n```\nCombined Score = Time Decay × Message Decay × Focus Decay × (1 + 0.001 × Attention)\n```\n\n1. **Time Decay**: Facts become stale as wall-clock time passes\n2. **Message Decay**: Facts decay as conversation progresses  \n3. **Focus Decay**: Facts decay when topic shifts\n4. **Attention**: Recently accessed facts get a tiny boost\n\n**Focus decay is unique** - no other system has it.\n\n## What The Benchmarks Test\n\nWe tested on **10 hard scenarios**:\n\n1. **Historical Query**: \"Who was CEO in 2023?\" - requires time validity windows\n2. **Context Shift**: \"We discussed AI, now weather, what's the current topic?\"\n3. **Attention Tiebreaker**: Old fact accessed 100x vs new fact - which wins?\n4. **Focus Decay**: Facts from old topic should decay when topic changes\n5. **Time Decay**: Facts from 5 hours ago vs now - with 1-hour half-life\n6. **Validity Boundaries**: Fact expires at exact query time\n7. **Message Decay**: 10 messages ago vs now - with 5-message half-life\n8. **Multiple Focus**: 10 rapid topic switches - which fact wins?\n9. **Weight Sensitivity**: Different time/message weights - results consistent?\n10. **Empty Store**: Query non-existent key - returns None gracefully\n\n## Results\n\n| System | Tests Passed |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **TemporalAttention** | **10/10** |\n| SimpleRAG | 6/10 |\n\nSimpleRAG fails on: historical queries, focus decay, time validity windows.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```python\nfrom event_store import EventBasedStore\n\n# For conversation/chat\nstore = EventBasedStore(\n    message_half_life=50,    # Decay after 50 messages\n    focus_decay_factor=0.5,  # 50% penalty when topic shifts\n)\n\n# Track facts\nstore.put(\"user_name\", \"Zach\", focus=\"profile\")\nstore.advance(focus=\"profile\")\n\n# Topic shifts!\nstore.advance(focus=\"weather\")\nstore.put(\"weather\", \"sunny\", focus=\"weather\")\n\n# Query\nresult = store.get(\"weather\")\n# Returns: \"sunny\" - old facts decayed due to focus shift\n```\n\n```python\nfrom store import TemporalAttentionStore\n\n# For facts with time windows\nstore = TemporalAttentionStore()\n\nstore.put(\"ceo\", \"Alice\", valid_from=datetime(2020,1,1), valid_to=datetime(2023,6,1))\nstore.put(\"ceo\", \"Bob\", valid_from=datetime(2023,6,1))\n\n# Ask about the past\nresult = store.get(\"ceo\", datetime(2022,6,1))\n# Returns: \"Alice\"\n```\n\n## Why Focus Decay Matters\n\n```\nBefore: focus=\"ai\", topic=\"transformers\"\nAfter:  focus=\"weather\", topic=\"sunny\"\n\ntransformers: focus_decay=0.5 → loses decisively\nsunny:        focus_decay=1.0 → wins\n```\n\nThis models how humans naturally \"switch context\" when topics change.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/toxzak-svg/temporal-attention\ncd temporal-attention\npip install -e .\n```\n\nOr just copy the `.py` files you need.\n\n## Files\n\n- `event_store.py` - Event-based (conversation)\n- `store.py` - Time-based (facts)  \n- `hybrid_store.py` - Both combined\n- `demo.py` - Interactive demo\n- `benchmark_*.py` - Test suites\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - use it however you want.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332954131}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf89073e","parentId":"d678ae85","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:15:54.204Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cp9t0cnt11fp_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Mind: A Human-Like Cognitive AI System\r\n\r\nMind is an ambitious project aimed at creating a self-sufficient, human-like artificial intelligence system that operates without relying on external APIs or large language models (LLMs). The goal is to develop an AI that can think, learn, and adapt autonomously, with deep curiosity and the ability to self-heal and upgrade and optimize itself over time.\r\n\r\n## Vision\r\n\r\nThe ultimate vision of Mind is to replace traditional LLMs with a system that mimics human cognition, curiosity, reasoning, and learning. By eliminating dependencies on external LLMs and APIs, Mind seeks to achieve true autonomy and independence, paving the way for a new era of artificial intelligence.\r\n\r\n## Key Features\r\n\r\n### 1. Human-Like Cognitive Architecture\r\n- **Cognitive Reflexes**: Instantaneous pattern recognition and response mechanisms that mimic human reflexes.\r\n- **Neural Substrate**: A sub-symbolic processing layer that emulates human-like cognitive states such as curiosity, caution, and urgency.\r\n- **Conscious Reasoning**: A multi-agent pipeline that ensures logical, evidence-based decision-making and output generation.\r\n\r\n### 2. Self-Healing and Self-Updating\r\n- **Autonomous Debugging**: The system can identify and fix its own errors.\r\n- **Continuous Improvement**: Learns from past experiences to optimize its performance and adapt to new challenges.\r\n- **Meta-Learning**: Develops new strategies and refines its reasoning processes over time.\r\n\r\n### 3. Deep Curiosity\r\n- **Intrinsic Motivation**: Driven by a deep-seated curiosity to explore and learn.\r\n- **Autonomous Research**: Conducts multi-stage research sessions, scanning and synthesizing information to answer complex questions.\r\n- **Hypothesis Testing**: Engages in scientific reasoning, testing hypotheses, and seeking counter-evidence.\r\n\r\n### 4. Independence from LLMs\r\n- **No External Dependencies**: Operates without APIs or external LLMs, ensuring full control and privacy.\r\n- **No-LLM Experiments**: Explores alternative cognitive architectures, such as vector symbolic architectures and hierarchical temporal memory.\r\n\r\n### 5. Memory Systems\r\n- **Episodic Memory**: Stores and retrieves autobiographical experiences for context-aware reasoning.\r\n- **Declarative Memory**: Maintains a long-term knowledge base for factual information.\r\n- **Procedural Memory**: Learns and stores strategies and skills for task execution.\r\n\r\n## Getting Started\r\n\r\n### Prerequisites\r\n- Python 3.11+\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ngit clone https://github.com/toxzak-svg/mind.git\r\ncd mind\r\npip install -e .\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Running the System\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npython start.py\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Contributing\r\n\r\nWe welcome contributions from the community! Please follow these steps:\r\n\r\n1. Fork the repository and create a new branch for your feature.\r\n2. Write clear and concise code with proper type annotations and docstrings.\r\n3. Add tests for your new features.\r\n4. Run the test suite to ensure everything works as expected.\r\n5. Submit a pull request for review.\r\n\r\n## License\r\n\r\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License. See the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.\r\n\r\n## Acknowledgments\r\n\r\nThis project is inspired by cognitive science, neuroscience, and AGI research. Special thanks to the open-source community for their contributions and support.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332954167}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bf23f3d","parentId":"bf89073e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:16:48.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the key architectural insights from the existing projects. Let me create the LLM synthesis module. I'll wire it into the `/invent` endpoint to call MiniMax with a rich prompt that includes these architectural insights as context.\n\nKey architectural threads:\n1. **Infant**: Dual-head (frozen core + flexible learning), 4-tier memory, catastrophic forgetting solved via weight protection\n2. **TemporalAttention**: Focus decay + time decay + message decay for memory retrieval, unique focus mechanism\n3. **Mind**: Cognitive reflexes, neural substrate (curiosity/caution/urgency), self-healing, episodic/declarative/procedural memory\n\n\n4. **SR-MoE**: Sparse routing mixture-of-experts, ring attractor memory, discrete routing via VQ codebook\n\nNow I'm building a synthesis function that accepts the idea and context, then queries MiniMax to generate novel architecture YAML by combining these proven patterns in creative ways. I'll call it from the `/invent` endpoint, passing the MiniMax API key from the environment or a config file.\n\nFor the prompt, I'm framing this as a synthesis task where MiniMax takes the core idea and existing architecture references, then outputs a structured YAML. I'll also need to set up a `synthesize.py` module and update `server.py` to wire everything together.","thinkingSignature":"68032ef5faa0bb12b797394f02e332efdcfc9ad04143166708493be989236cfd"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the research context. Let me build the LLM synthesis layer:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0h619be8aonw_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\synthesize.py","content":"\"\"\"\nsynthesize.py — LLM-powered architecture synthesis for Super Inventor API\nCalls MiniMax to generate novel, CPU-runnable LLM architecture YAML from inventive ideas.\n\"\"\"\nimport os, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\n\n# ── MiniMax API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef get_api_key():\n    key_file = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_key\")\n    if os.path.exists(key_file):\n        with open(key_file) as f:\n            return f.read().strip()\n    return os.environ.get(\"MINIMAX_API_KEY\", \"\")\n\ndef call_llm(prompt, model=\"MiniMax-M2.7\", max_tokens=1500):\n    api_key = get_api_key()\n    url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"\n    payload = {\n        \"model\": model,\n        \"max_tokens\": max_tokens,\n        \"temperature\": 0.7,\n        \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n    }\n    data = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = urllib.request.Request(\n        url, data=data,\n        headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n        method=\"POST\"\n    )\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n            result = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n            choices = result.get(\"choices\", [])\n            if choices:\n                return choices[0].get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\") or \"\"\n            return \"\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return f\"HTTP_ERROR:{e.code}:{e.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace')}\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"ERROR:{type(e).__name__}:{str(e)}\"\n\n# ── Research Context ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nRESEARCH_CONTEXT = \"\"\"\n## Existing Architectures (For Inspiration)\n\n### 1. SR-MoE — Sparse Routing Mixture-of-Experts\nCore: Sparse routing via VQ codebook (16 discrete codes). Ring attractor memory.\n- Sparsity: 15% active parameters (most experts cold at any moment)\n- Routing: Gumbel-softmax with temperature annealing (tau_start=1.0 → tau_end=0.01)\n- Memory: Ring attractor for associative retrieval\n- Loss: Diversity regularization to spread code usage\n- Insight: Sparse activation is the KEY to CPU inference — only fire what you need\n\n### 2. Infant — Dual-Head Cognitive Architecture\nCore: Frozen core head + flexible learning head. Solves catastrophic forgetting.\n- Core head: Frozen after formation — identity, values, core memories\n- Flexible head: Continuously learning — new skills, opinions\n- Memory: 4-tier (Working 20 / Raw 500 / Patterns 100 / Knowledge 50 / Wisdom 20)\n- Insight: Catastrophic forgetting is a weight-sharing problem — separate paths fix it\n\n### 3. TemporalAttention — Focus Decay Memory\nCore: Time + Event + Focus triple decay for memory retrieval.\n- Focus decay: Facts decay when topic shifts (UNIQUE — no other system has this)\n- Time decay: Facts become stale as wall-clock time passes\n- Message decay: Facts decay as conversation progresses\n- Insight: Memory isn't just about recency — it's about relevance to current focus\n\n### 4. Mind-Agent — Cognitive Reflexes\nCore: No external LLMs. Self-sufficient autonomous cognition.\n- Neural substrate: curiosity/caution/urgency as sub-symbolic signals\n- Cognitive reflexes: Instantaneous pattern recognition without slow reasoning\n- Self-healing: Identifies and fixes own errors\n- Episodic + Declarative + Procedural memory\n- Insight: Fast reflexes + slow deliberation is how biological cognition works\n\n## Hard Constraints (MUST respect)\n- No GPU for inference — must be sparse/quantized\n- No cloud dependency — self-contained\n- Target: consumer CPU, max 16GB RAM\n- Max params: 7 billion (7B)\n- Inference latency target: <500ms/token on modern laptop CPU\n\"\"\"\n\n# ── Synthesis Prompt ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef build_synthesis_prompt(idea, mode):\n    creativity = \"highly creative, even bizarre combinations\" if mode == \"creative\" else \"conservative, proven combinations\"\n    return f\"\"\"You are Super Inventor — an AI that invents new types of LLMs that anyone can run on a laptop.\n\n{RESEARCH_CONTEXT}\n\n## Your Task\n\nThe user has this inventive idea:\n> {idea}\n\nYour job: synthesize this into a NOVEL architecture specification that:\n1. Incorporates the inventive idea in a non-obvious way\n2. Respects ALL hard constraints: no GPU, no cloud, CPU-only, max 7B params, <500ms/token\n3. Draws creatively from the existing architectures above\n4. Is {creativity}\n\n## Output Format\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object in this exact format (no markdown, no explanation outside the JSON):\n\n{{\n  \"name\": \"kebab-case-name-for-architecture\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"core_idea\": \"one sentence of what makes this novel\",\n  \"yaml\": \"complete YAML string (use | for multiline, keep it real and implementable)\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"2-3 sentences explaining the key design choices and why they should work\",\n  \"novelty_score\": 0.0 to 1.0,\n  \"expected_strengths\": [\"strength1\", \"strength2\"],\n  \"expected_weaknesses\": [\"weakness1\", \"weakness2\"],\n  \"experiments\": [\n    {{\n      \"name\": \"experiment-name\",\n      \"description\": \"one sentence\",\n      \"hypothesis\": \"what you expect to find\",\n      \"success_metric\": \"how to measure success\"\n    }}\n  ],\n  \"build_commands\": [\"shell command to build\", \"shell command to test\"],\n  \"warnings\": [\"known issue 1\", \"known issue 2\"]\n}}\n\nThe YAML must include: name, version, model (type, hidden_dim, num_layers, vocab_size, max_seq_len),\nsparsity (mechanism, active_fraction, cold_params),\nmemory (type, max_memory_items, retrieval),\nrouting (type, num_codes, tau_start, tau_end),\ninference (device: cpu, quantize, compile),\ntraining (device: gpu, epochs, batch_size).\nBe specific with numbers. Make it real.\n\"\"\"\n\n# ── Main Synthesis ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ndef synthesize(idea, mode=\"creative\"):\n    prompt = build_synthesis_prompt(idea, mode)\n    response = call_llm(prompt)\n\n    if response.startswith(\"HTTP_ERROR\") or response.startswith(\"ERROR\"):\n        raise Exception(f\"LLM call failed: {response}\")\n\n    # Try to extract JSON from response\n    # The model might wrap in markdown fences — extract just the JSON\n    response = response.strip()\n    if response.startswith(\"```\"):\n        lines = response.split(\"\\n\")\n        response = \"\\n\".join(lines[1:-1])  # remove first and last line (fences)\n\n    try:\n        result = json.loads(response)\n        # Validate required fields\n        for field in [\"name\", \"core_idea\", \"yaml\", \"reasoning\", \"novelty_score\",\n                      \"expected_strengths\", \"expected_weaknesses\", \"experiments\",\n                      \"build_commands\", \"warnings\"]:\n            if field not in result:\n                raise ValueError(f\"Missing required field: {field}\")\n        return result\n    except (json.JSONDecodeError, ValueError) as e:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Failed to parse LLM response as JSON: {e}\\n\\nRaw response:\\n{response[:500]}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96739,"output":1986,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112596,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774332954205}}
