{"type":"message","id":"37f0fb43","parentId":"be86bfd8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:22:02.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also check if the thinking tags are properly matched. The raw response showed `<think>\\nWe need to create...` without a closing `</think>`. The regex `re.sub(r'<think>.*?</think>', ...)` would not match because there's no `</think>`. Let me think... Actually `re.DOTALL` makes `.` match newlines too, so `<think>.*?</think>` won't match if there's no closing tag. But the thinking block might have been cut off mid-stream by the tokenizer or something.\n\nLet me also add a fallback: if no closing tag, just remove everything from `<think>` to the end:","thinkingSignature":"a6e08cf53ad4d5992ac8b5a34b31d68f744c57caa5f9f614ca9564a68642525c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qhswmo8pbh8l_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\synthesize.py","old_string":"    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    response = re.sub(r'<think>.*?</think>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()","new_string":"    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    response = re.sub(r'<think>.*?</think>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    # Fallback: if thinking block was cut off, remove from <think> to end of string\n    if '<think>' in response and '</think>' not in response:\n        response = response[response.index('</think>')+10:].strip()\n    if '<think>' in response:\n        response = response.split('</think>', 1)[-1].strip()"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95931,"output":357,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110159,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774333312345}}
