{"type":"message","id":"b841aef6","parentId":"92688cff","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:22:23.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the fallback logic is a bit off. If `</think>` is in the string but the regex didn't match, that means the regex is not working. Let me think again.\n\nThe raw response starts with `<think>\\nWe need to create...`. There is no `</think>` in it. The regex `r'<think>.*?</think>'` won't match anything (returns original string unchanged). Then we hit the fallback `if '<think>' in response and '</think>' not in response` — yes, `<think>` IS in the response, `</think>` is NOT. So we do `response[response.index('</think>')+10:]`. But `response.index('</think>')` would RAISE ValueError since `</think>` is not there! That's why I put it after the regex that would have already removed it if present. \n\nLet me reconsider the order — I should search for `</think>` first before trying to index it, and if it's not there, I can just strip everything after `<think>`. But actually, the cleanest approach is to use a greedy regex that matches from the start of the thinking block all the way to the end of the response, which handles the case where the closing tag might be missing entirely.","thinkingSignature":"f519ae757c23ed6272f83b6ee3137dc1092e9d264710e1f677661781db09272b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8h88j78vve92_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\synthesize.py","old_string":"    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    response = re.sub(r'<think>.*?</think>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    # Fallback: if thinking block was cut off, remove from <think> to end of string\n    if '<think>' in response and '</think>' not in response:\n        response = response[response.index('</think>')+10:].strip()\n    if '<think>' in response:\n        response = response.split('</think>', 1)[-1].strip()","new_string":"    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    # Remove <think>...</think> blocks (handles both complete and cut-off blocks)\n    # Greedy: from <think> to end, then take everything after the last </think>\n    if '<think>' in response:\n        parts = response.split('<think>')\n        after = '<think>'.join(parts[1:])  # rejoin without first <think>\n        if '</think>' in after:\n            after = after.split('</think>', 1)[-1]\n        response = after.strip()\n        response = '<think>'.join([parts[0]] + ['</think>'.join(['']) + after])  # reconstruct cleanly\n        # Simple: just take everything AFTER the last </think> in the string\n        last_thtag = response.rfind('</think>')\n        if last_thtag != -1:\n            response = response[last_thtag + 10:].strip()\n        else:\n            # No closing tag at all — take everything after first <think>\n            first_thtag = response.find('<think>')\n            if first_thtag != -1:\n                response = response[first_thtag + 10:].strip()"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96319,"output":689,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110879,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774333322779}}
