{"type":"message","id":"187cd12a","parentId":"071d5483","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:24:17.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the key I used was `sk-cp-boO3RF_...` which starts with `sk-`. That looks like an OpenAI key format, not a MiniMax API key. Let me check if MiniMax uses the same format for API keys. Also, I should check what the actual key format is. Looking at the sandbox call_llm.py, it might use a different base URL.Let me check the sandbox's call_llm.py to understand how it works.","thinkingSignature":"bfbc0836332d49be9b9b0e858479b2a29658ace7ea44f793983c017fbcb17c47"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a7a7dpajbbwr_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\call_llm.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96093,"output":141,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110105,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774333452469}}
{"type":"message","id":"c5709ce0","parentId":"187cd12a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:24:18.002Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a7a7dpajbbwr_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nllm.py — clean LLM call wrapper for sandbox pulse\nCalls MiniMax-M2.7 API and writes response to .llm_response.txt\nPython subprocess avoids PowerShell heredoc/encoding issues.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\nRESPONSE_FILE = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_response.txt\")\n\ndef get_api_key():\n    with open(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_key\")) as f:\n        return f.read().strip()\n\ndef call_llm(prompt, model=\"MiniMax-M2.7\", max_tokens=1200):\n    api_key = get_api_key()\n    url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"\n    payload = {\"model\": model, \"max_tokens\": max_tokens, \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]}\n    data = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=data, headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n            result = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n            choices = result.get(\"choices\", [])\n            if choices:\n                content = choices[0].get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n                return content or \"\"\n            return \"\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return f\"HTTP_ERROR:{e.code}:{e.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace')}\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"ERROR:{type(e).__name__}:{str(e)}\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python llm.py <prompt_file>\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    with open(sys.argv[1], encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        prompt = f.read()\n    result = call_llm(prompt)\n    # Write to file to avoid Windows console encoding issues (Greek, emoji, etc.)\n    with open(RESPONSE_FILE, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        f.write(result)\n    # Also print to stderr for logging\n    print(f\"LLM response written to {RESPONSE_FILE}: {len(result)} chars\", file=sys.stderr)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333457946}}
{"type":"message","id":"163d0259","parentId":"c5709ce0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:24:27.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the sandbox's call_llm.py uses the same URL and format as what I wrote. But the API key `sk-cp-boO3RF_...` looks like an OpenAI API key format, not a MiniMax API key. Let me check the key format.\n\nActually, MiniMax API keys can start with different prefixes. The key format might be different. Let me test the direct API call.\n\nActually, let me look at the key more carefully. `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0`\n \nI'm realizing this key might be for a different service entirely since the prefix `sk-cp-` doesn't match the standard MiniMax format. Let me just test the API directly to see if the key actually works, rather than guessing based on the format.","thinkingSignature":"73184d68acb8c4110207b68ec43be5be6a4893ff858643728d1a50bcde09cd86"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e7v2adcnt1sl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python \"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\test_llm_direct.py\" 2>&1","timeout":35000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96772,"output":284,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110927,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774333458009}}
