{"type":"message","id":"51745828","parentId":"764332d9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:24:58.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API is working. But there's a `<think>` tag in the response. The MiniMax model is outputting its reasoning with `<think>` tags. So the raw content from the API includes `<think>...</think>` tags that I need to strip.\n\nThe response contains:\n```\n'\\nThe user wants me to say hello in one word...Hello!...\n```\n\nWait, looking at this more carefully - the actual `content` field is:\n```\n\"Hello!\"\n```\n\nBut it also has a `<think>` block in the response object. The `<think>` tags are part of the content, not separate fields.\n\nWait, looking at the full response:\n\n\n```json\n{\"id\":\"...\",\"choices\":[{\"index\":0,\"finish_reason\":\"stop\",\"message\":{\"content\":\"\\nThe user wants me to say hello in one word. ...\\n\\nHello!','role':'assistant',...\n```\n\nSo the actual content includes the reasoning text AND then \"Hello!\" at the end. The `</think>` comes right before the actual answer. I need to strip the `<think>...</think>` thinking block from the content string and only return what comes after it.\n\nThe API call already handles this by extracting the content field from the response, but the thinking tags are embedded in that content itself. The actual clean answer is just \"Hello!\" - the rest is the model's reasoning process that I need to remove.\n\nLooking at the raw response, the content starts with `<think>` tags and reasoning text, then `</think>` appears right before the actual response, followed by \"Hello!\" and the metadata. So I need to parse out everything after the last `</think>` marker to get just the useful response.","thinkingSignature":"2c0d27d488cc7fa4fef4d88468813bea5ca25392071971cd64fe7536e1f3b25b"},{"type":"text","text":"The API works. The content has `<think>` tags before the actual answer. Let me update the parse:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2me9msty1rj0_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\synthesize.py","old_string":"    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    if '<think>' in response:\n        parts = response.split('<think>')\n        after = '<think>'.join(parts[1:])\n        if '</think>' in after:\n            after = after.split('</think>', 1)[-1]\n        else:\n            after = after.strip()\n        response = (parts[0] + after).strip()\n    # Extract JSON: find first '{' and last '}'\n    first_brace = response.find('{')\n    last_brace = response.rfind('}')\n    if first_brace != -1 and last_brace != -1 and last_brace > first_brace:\n        response = response[first_brace:last_brace+1]","new_string":"    # Strip <thinking>...</thinking> tags (MiniMax reasoning tags)\n    response = re.sub(r'<thinking>.*?</thinking>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    response = re.sub(r'<think>.*?</think>', '', response, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\n    # Extract JSON: find first '{' and last '}' after stripping thinking tags\n    first_brace = response.find('{')\n    last_brace = response.rfind('}')\n    if first_brace != -1 and last_brace != -1 and last_brace > first_brace:\n        response = response[first_brace:last_brace+1]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96460,"output":722,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111053,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774333471381}}
