{"type":"message","id":"0b05d945","parentId":"74dc7fb7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:48:09.321Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still getting empty response. The JSON extraction is giving an empty string. Let me debug further — let me add some logging to see what the raw LLM response looks like for the full synthesis prompt.","thinkingSignature":"3b58e8322054751a42c7e4fe79ff91786eafd00e696aac9c021e4f5080293358"},{"type":"text","text":"Still empty responses from the LLM. Let me debug directly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6p59nxqzoye3_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\dev\\SuperInventor\\debug_llm.py","content":"\"\"\"Debug LLM synthesis directly\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, json, re, urllib.request, urllib.error\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\dev\\SuperInventor')\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = r'C:\\dev\\SuperInventor'\n\ndef get_api_key():\n    with open(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_key\")) as f:\n        return f.read().strip()\n\nprompt = \"\"\"You are Super Inventor — an AI that invents new types of LLMs that anyone can run on a laptop.\n\n## Existing Architectures (For Inspiration)\n\n### 1. SR-MoE — Sparse Routing Mixture-of-Experts\nCore: Sparse routing via VQ codebook (16 discrete codes). Ring attractor memory.\n- Sparsity: 15% active parameters (most experts cold at any moment)\n- Routing: Gumbel-softmax with temperature annealing (tau_start=1.0 → tau_end=0.01)\n- Memory: Ring attractor for associative retrieval\n- Loss: Diversity regularization to spread code usage\n- Insight: Sparse activation is the KEY to CPU inference — only fire what you need\n\n### 2. Infant — Dual-Head Cognitive Architecture\nCore: Frozen core head + flexible learning head. Solves catastrophic forgetting.\n- Core head: Frozen after formation — identity, values, core memories\n- Flexible head: Continuously learning — new skills, opinions\n\n### 3. TemporalAttention — Focus Decay Memory\nCore: Time + Event + Focus triple decay for memory retrieval.\n- Focus decay: Facts decay when topic shifts (UNIQUE — no other system has this)\n\n### 4. Mind-Agent — Cognitive Reflexes\nCore: No external LLMs. Self-sufficient autonomous cognition.\n- Neural substrate: curiosity/caution/urgency as sub-symbolic signals\n\n## Hard Constraints (MUST respect)\n- No GPU for inference — must be sparse/quantized\n- No cloud dependency — self-contained\n- Target: consumer CPU, max 16GB RAM\n- Max params: 7 billion (7B)\n- Inference latency target: <500ms/token\n\n## Your Task\n\nThe user has this inventive idea:\n> use focus decay from temporal attention to route which sparse experts activate\n\nYour job: synthesize this into a NOVEL architecture specification.\n\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object in this exact format (no markdown, no explanation):\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"kebab-case-name\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"core_idea\": \"one sentence of what makes this novel\",\n  \"yaml\": \"complete YAML\",\n  \"reasoning\": \"2-3 sentences\",\n  \"novelty_score\": 0.5,\n  \"expected_strengths\": [\"s1\", \"s2\"],\n  \"expected_weaknesses\": [\"w1\"],\n  \"experiments\": [{\"name\": \"e1\", \"description\": \"d1\", \"hypothesis\": \"h1\", \"success_metric\": \"m1\"}],\n  \"build_commands\": [\"cmd1\"],\n  \"warnings\": [\"warn1\"]\n}\"\"\"\n\napi_key = get_api_key()\nurl = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"\npayload = {\n    \"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    \"max_tokens\": 2000,\n    \"temperature\": 0.7,\n    \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n}\ndata = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\nreq = urllib.request.Request(\n    url, data=data,\n    headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n    method=\"POST\"\n)\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n        result = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n        choices = result.get(\"choices\", [])\n        if choices:\n            content = choices[0].get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\") or \"\"\n            print(f\"RAW RESPONSE ({len(content)} chars):\")\n            print(repr(content[:300]))\n            print(\"---\")\n            # Try to parse\n            content = content.strip()\n            if '<thinking>' in content:\n                print(\"HAS <thinking>\")\n            if '</think>' in content:\n                print(\"HAS </think>\")\n            # Try extraction\n            if '<think>' in content:\n                parts = content.split('</think>', 1)\n                print(f\"Parts before </think>: {repr(parts[0][:100])}\")\n                if len(parts) > 1:\n                    after = parts[1].strip()\n                    print(f\"After </think>: {repr(after[:200])}\")\n                    first_brace = after.find('{')\n                    last_brace = after.rfind('}')\n                    print(f\"Braces: first={first_brace}, last={last_brace}\")\nexcept urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n    print(f\"HTTPError {e.code}: {e.read().decode()}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98405,"output":1154,"cacheRead":13871,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113430,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774338462807}}
